text:
according to the times, cambridge analytica bought the data from aleksandr kogan, a russian-american academic. kogan, who told facebook he was conducting academic research, built a facebook personality quiz app called "thisisyourdigitalife." when users downloaded the app, it scraped all of their available facebook data, including their friends, their likes and where they lived.

more than a quarter-million facebook users downloaded the app, which also exploited a facebook vulnerability that allowed it to to collect most of the same data from the friends of those who downloaded it. by prying into the friends lists of those who made the download, kogan was able to get data from more than 50 million people.

throughout 2015 and into 2016, the cruz campaign paid cambridge analytica almost $6 million for data that the campaign used for what it called "psychographic targeting," which supposedly allowed the campaign to tailor its message to specific voters in places like iowa and new hampshire, where single voters can make a big difference. using data from the firm, the campaign built profiles of potential voters, prioritizing those who fit in categories such as "stoic traditionalist" and "true believer". in december 2015, the same month the guardian revealed cambridge analytica and kogan's data harvesting practices, cruz campaign spokesman rick tyler called the company a "market leader and the best in the field." despite tyler's claim that the cruz campaign stopped using the firm's data in early 2016, it kept paying cambridge analytica until june of that year, a month after cruz suspended his campaign. after cruz dropped out of the race, the firm began working with trump, supporting him through november's general election against hillary clinton.

stephen young
dallas observer

text:
in his first post-white house interviews, steve bannon, the rightwing ideologue who helped propel donald trump to the white house, made clear that he had no intention of going quietly. - i’ve got my hands back on my weapons, the former white house chief strategist, who returned as executive chairman of breitbart news late friday afternoon, told the weekly standard. - i built a f***ing machine at breitbart. and now i’m about to go back, knowing what i know, and we’re about to rev that machine up. and rev it up we will do.

just hours after his departure from the trump administration became public, breitbart, whose traffic and advertising have fallen significantly since trump’s election, trumpeted the return of their “populist hero” on its homepage. - the populist-nationalist movement got a lot stronger today, breitbart editor-in-chief alex marlow said in the publication’s announcement post. - breitbart gained an executive chairman with his finger on the pulse of the trump agenda.

the fall of steve bannon is a win for the globalists. but will it last?

also on friday, the once-again head of breitbart told bloomberg news: - if there’s any confusion out there, let me clear it up: i’m leaving the white house and going to war for trump against his opponents – on capitol hill, in the media, and in corporate america.

the 63-year-old also retains the backing of hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. the pair met on wednesday to plot their future plans, bloomberg reported.

julia carrie wong
the guardian

text:
ho fatto questa illustrazione per la casa delle donne @luchaysiesta .
a un anno dall’apertura della querelle sul fallimento di atac, la casa delle donne lucha y siesta è in vendita. l'atac ha richiesto la liberazione dello stabile.
la chiusura di lucha sarebbe una perdita gigantesca, una perdita che non riguarda solo le donne, ma tutt* ed è necessario agire per evitarla. "per chi non la conosce, lucha y siesta è un progetto ibrido tra centro antiviolenza, casa rifugio e casa di semi autonomia, ma è anche molto di più. uno spazio politico femminista e un punto di riferimento e di autorevolezza in cui si alimentano socialità, cultura e immaginazione. da 11 anni, la casa fornisce accoglienza e sostegno ai percorsi di autonomia e uscita dalla violenza per donne e bambine/i in difficoltà; sono circa 1200 le donne sostenute nei loro percorsi di fuoriuscita dalla violenza in questo decennio; più di 140 donne e 60 minori ci hanno abitato per periodi più o meno lunghi. è un luogo fondamentale perché in tutta roma il comune dispone in maniera diretta di soli 20 posti per accogliere donne che escono da situazioni di violenza, quando la convenzione di istanbul ne prevede per la città circa 300. lucha y siesta ne ha 14, il 60% dei posti di tutto il territorio comunale."
questi dati sono tratti dal comunicato della casa.

#luchaysiestanonsivende
#luchaliberatutte
#lacasasiamotutte #ritapetruccioli #illustration #pupazze #feminism #metoo  #girl #luchaysiesta #strongwoman

"per chi non la conosce, lucha y siesta è un progetto ibrido tra centro antiviolenza, casa rifugio e casa di semi autonomia, ma è anche molto di più. uno spazio politico femminista e un punto di riferimento e di autorevolezza in cui si alimentano socialità, cultura e immaginazione. da 11 anni, la casa fornisce accoglienza e sostegno ai percorsi di autonomia e uscita dalla violenza per donne e bambine/i in difficoltà; sono circa 1200 le donne sostenute nei loro percorsi di fuoriuscita dalla violenza in questo decennio; più di 140 donne e 60 minori ci hanno abitato per periodi più o meno lunghi. è un luogo fondamentale perché in tutta roma il comune dispone in maniera diretta di soli 20 posti per accogliere donne che escono da situazioni di violenza, quando la convenzione di istanbul ne prevede per la città circa 300. lucha y siesta ne ha 14, il 60% dei posti di tutto il territorio comunale."
questi dati sono tratti dal comunicato della casa.

text:
- this was steve bannon's baby, said former contractor christopher wylie, who described cambridge analytica as "bannon's arsenal of weaponry to wage a culture war on america using military strategies."
.
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
there is a healing power in creative expression. 
yesterday i had a papsmeer. when you've had a very crappy childhood sexual abuse experience certain things are painful triggers.. this was definitely one of them.
our bodies store memories physically, muscle memory. the flood of memories and bodily sensations can be as traumatic as the original incident. they threaten to overwhelm and capsize you with the intensity of each wave/flood of memory.

i always yearn to cut it out, cut myself open and just pour out the painful sensations so they cannot take up space in my skin my body my heart my soul and their permanent residence;my mind!

art has become this escape, i'll mindlessly or frantically pick up my materials and put every unnamed, unprocessed, unsure emotion onto paper. i cannot always verbalise the feelings. but the paper willingly takes them, holds them and transforms them from murky, dark, fearbased anxiety into a form i can recognise.

i was too young and vulnerable to understand what was happening, my adult self breaks to pieces with each intrusive memory, desperate to shield my child self from the horrors no child should even know exists.

complex post traumatic shock syndrome (no longer classed as a disorder but a symptom of trauma) is manageable. it is brutal. it can feel overwhelming beyond measure but your mind can heal from those brutal wounds. we might limp slightly but broken bones heal stronger and broken souls heal fiercer!
#metoo #nfiniteheart #mentalhealth #cptsd #cptssrecovery #ptsd #ptss #trauma #mentalillness #chronicillness #healing #art #arttherapy #creative #musclememory #selfcare #community #survivor #triggers

text:
life after|i am so blessed to say that my article, titled “life after sexual abuse” has been published in injoy magazine @crystal_injoy_magazine !!! it’s a blessing to be able to share parts of my story to help someone else. here is an excerpt from the publication...”i was 11 years old visiting a close relatives house with my immediate family. i found myself  in the back room of the house alone; one of the young men enters the room & sat me on his lap. i didn’t really think nothing of it because i knew this family member very well with no prior issues. he proceeded to cover my ear stick his tongue in it while touching & rubbing on me inappropriately. instantly; i became numb, i felt ashamed and i was afraid. it lasted about 5-10 mins but it seemed like forever. he took me off his lap and i couldn’t comprehend what just happened to me! i didn’t know what to do. i felt frozen in fear! in that moment, i decided to not tell anyone. i just kept it to myself. before particular incident happened, i had already been sexually abused starting at the age of 5 by other young men. as i got older; i felt the shame of it, the pain from it and started to feel like i didn’t belong. i was angry at my abusers and wanted to know why they would do this to me. why would they violate my body.” thank you so much to ms. crystal for this opportunity! a special thanks to @kid.august for taking very beautiful photos that help tell my story, to my sissy @iamsarahmatthews for the wonderful design layout and to @oldmillcafe_ec for the eclectic location for the shoot! #tellyourstory #beyondthebarriers of #depression there is #hope
#blackgirlmagic #model #modeling #modellife #blackgirlsrock #melanin  #myblackisbeautiful #baltimore #dc #bmore #dmv #naturalbeauty  #brownskin #darkskin  #knowyourworth #melaninmovement #melaninmagic #selflove #instablogger #hopestillstands #sexualabuse #survivor #storyteller #writersofinstagram #metoo

text:
don’t just aspire to make a living. .

aspire to make a difference. .

i spent 20 years working my tail off in the las vegas real estate market,  and my husband and i made a great living. .

it afforded us choices and one was to retire and pursue a chance to make a difference. .

often times we don’t even know how one person can do that.  but it’s the little’s acts of kindness that creates the ripple effect of change we are seeking in the world. .

now, a smile or a kind gesture isn’t going to fix all of our worlds problems but it just may change one persons day. .

look at that. you already started to make a difference! .

i challenge you to start putting the wheels in motion to aspire to make a difference anyway you can.

kriti sanon: i’m glad that #metoo happened and shook things up
#
image source - instagramevery industry is mired with some or the other controversy. bollywood too has been mired with several issues since time immemorial. harassment at the workplace is one of them. last year, the much needed #metoo movement hit the indian shores and eventually it revealed the ugly side of the show business where power and money call the shots.the movement led to several renowned names making its way the alleged harassers’ list. filmmaker sajid khan too was named and shamed by several women and that ultimately led to him to walking out of ‘housefull 4′. he was replaced by farhad samji as the director. kriti sanon, who is one of the actresses featuring in ‘housefull 4’, recently opened up about the movement.kriti, in an interview to mumbai mirror said, “i’m a big feminist and #metoo is the greatest thing to happen to the film industry in a long time. it’s changed the way people look at things. now there’s fear that if you do something wrong, you can’t get away with it. i don’t know how much justice the survivors have got because sadly, there’s only so much you can do to prove your point because a lot of harassment…

text:
i was walking my children to school early morning, when a group of working men in a building site started whistling at me and making sexual noises. one of them shouted come on turn around love, don't be shy we don't bite. i was horrified that certain men think that this behaviour is acceptable. my poor children had to witness the filth that was said to me. these individuals choose a time when they know a woman is vulnerable and won't be able to fight back.

to make matters worse, when i explained to a friend what had happened she replied saying oh don't worry babe it's because your pretty, don't take no notice of it.

text:
wow. it's been a long time since i wrote here. there's no logical way to explain it but i've been feeling funny. tomorrow will be three years since i was beaten and raped. when i realised that it kind of made sense. you know, the funny feeling. so here i am again. battling through the pain. telling myself that tomorrow will be okay. .
.

text_retweet:
reposted from @vaccinesuncovered -  #repost @healthforourbabies
・・・
tmrw marks 1 year that we went to hayden’s pediatrician and she received her mmr vaccine. not a clue of the poison that was circulating her little one year old body, injuring her developing brain + causing 6th nerve palsy. you can listen to her vaccine injury story on our podcast, epi #6 (link above). please share her story with another mom who’s thinking of vaccinating her babies. ⁣⁣⁣
3 things:⁣⁣⁣
1. words can never express how incredibly thankful i am to all your beautiful heartfelt prayers. you downloading her podcast story, sharing it with friends has really helped spread awareness—it’s the most downloaded episode. ⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
2. what a blessing it is to see her recovery, it’s night + day! we recently went to a vision therapist who stated they couldn’t do any therapy until she was at least 4 years old. however, the risk of waiting this long is her injured right eye will think this is the new normal potentially causing the eye to permanently stay that way. so in the meantime, we’re doing the natural approach: eye patch, glasses, cod oil, vit c, eo’s + camu camu. we’ve seen a drastic improvement in her vision in the last month bc of camu camu so thank you for the referral!⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
3. i am still heartbroken that our world hasn’t woken up to the dangers of vaccines. how is this worldwide epidemic that is injuring and killing our children not national + international news? how is it that 70 dangerous vaccines that have to be given to our children including flu shots (or our kids can’t go to school) being mandated by our govt? how is it that vaccines which have little to no studies being created by pharma, approved by the cdc, placed into the hands of doctors, then injected into our precious perfect babies not alarming to every human on earth? how is this not going viral and demanding change like the #metoo or the women empowerment movement? if we don’t demand change from our govt to stop pharma + cdc, then we will continue to have generations of unhealthy children with cancer, allergies, autoimmune diseases, neurological damage, esotropia, sids (a cover up btw) + the list goes on. all for the sake of

text:
ĺa sororite en actes : samedi 16 mars, rencontre au sommet entre chloé delaume et clara dupuy morency !

aux mêmes éditions québécoises triptyque qui ont édité les désormais fameux « argonautes » de maggie nelson, a paru récemment « mère d’invention » : premier livre, essai brillant et protéiforme, de clara dupuis-morency. elle nous fait la joie de venir au monte-en-l’air lors de sa venue exceptionnelle en france. l’auteure, spécialiste de proust, y traite de son avortement puis de la naissance de ses jumelles, et d’une thèse défendue entre deux, y questionne la sororité, l’empowerment, le rapport féminin à la douleur, la médecine, la création, la maternité évidemment, de façon très personnelle et parfois inattendue. c’est drôle, effronté, enlevé, provoquant, tellurique, angoissé, viscéral, émouvant, intelligent, cérébral… en un mot… fé.mi.nin ! 
de ce non renoncement aux parties qui nous composent, ainsi mobilisées toutes entières dans l’écriture, on repense au texte de jana cerna qui nous avait tant plu : « pas dans le cul aujourd’hui », et à une certaine chloé delaume, du « cri du sablier » aux « sorcières de la république », qui a révolutionné la façon de concevoir lecture et écriture pour clara dupuy-morency.
et bien justement, chloé delaume nous fera l’honneur de sa présence. elle discutera avec clara dupuy morency, et présentera son nouveau livre, mes bien chères sœurs (le seuil) paru en mars 2019.  également hybride, il est à la fois un long billet d’humeur, un manifeste subjectif d’une troublante sincérité, investi d’expériences intimes et d’humour, sur la sororité, et un éloge des mouvements historiques qui ont produit ce qu’elle célèbre comme la « quatrième vague » du féminisme, au travers de l’hashtag #metoo. « mes bien chères sœurs » invite à danser sur l’eau et à invoquer de nos vœux l’apocalypse ! (si si !) #lemontenlair #montenlair #lemonteenlair #monteenlair #librairielemontenlair #chloedelaume #claradupuismorency #meredinvention #mesbiencheressoeurs #sororite #feminisme #librairie #librairieparis #paris #paris20 #75020 #estparisien #parisian #bouquins #menilmontant #livres #terrasse #bookshop #book #bookstagram#metoo

text:
here’s the reality: most sexual assaults and sexual violence are perpetrated by men, and arise within asymmetrical power dynamics. the aggressor occupies a more powerful or dominant position in relation to the victim. 
the vast majority of #metoo stories describe occurrences where men assert power bestowed on them by simply being a man. from homes to bars to school to state houses across the country to the white house, the stories we’ve all survived involve powerful, prominent men who use their positions and the perks of their power to seduce, coerce, manipulate, and attack. 
these men have what victims, who are in less powerful positions, want and need: a job, good grades, a promotion, a recommendation, an audition, a role in a movie, a place close to the center of power. they confuse and control by dangling enticements with one hand and wielding threats, implied or explicit, with the other. 
sexual abuse is all about power. we won’t stop calling attention to rape culture and those who benefit from it until it no longer exists.

reposted from @healthforourbabies -  tmrw marks 1 year that we went to hayden’s pediatrician and she received her mmr vaccine. not a clue of the poison that was circulating her little one year old body, injuring her developing brain + causing 6th nerve palsy. you can listen to her vaccine injury story on our podcast, epi #6 (link above). please share her story with another mom who’s thinking of vaccinating her babies. ⁣⁣⁣
3 things:⁣⁣⁣
1. words can never express how incredibly thankful i am to all your beautiful heartfelt prayers. you downloading her podcast story, sharing it with friends has really helped spread awareness—it’s the most downloaded episode. ⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
2. what a blessing it is to see her recovery, it’s night + day! we recently went to a vision therapist who stated they couldn’t do any therapy until she was at least 4 years old. however, the risk of waiting this long is her injured right eye will think this is the new normal potentially causing the eye to permanently stay that way. so in the meantime, we’re doing the natural approach: eye patch, glasses, cod oil, vit c, eo’s + camu camu. we’ve seen a drastic improvement in her vision in the last month bc of camu camu so thank you for the referral!⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
3. i am still heartbroken that our world hasn’t woken up to the dangers of vaccines. how is this worldwide epidemic that is injuring and killing our children not national + international news? how is it that 70 dangerous vaccines that have to be given to our children including flu shots (or our kids can’t go to school) being mandated by our govt? how is it that vaccines which have little to no studies being created by pharma, approved by the cdc, placed into the hands of doctors, then injected into our precious perfect babies not alarming to every human on earth? how is this not going viral and demanding change like the #metoo or the women empowerment movement? if we don’t demand change from our govt to stop pharma + cdc, then we will continue to have generations of unhealthy children with cancer, allergies, autoimmune diseases, neurological damage, esotropia, sids (a cover up btw) + the list goes on. all for the sake of money and greed. as mothers, w

text:
end it. volunteer. help. do something.
love. "to love at all is to be vulnerable. love anything and your heart will be wrung and possibly broken. if you want to make sure of keeping it intact you must give it to no one, not even an animal. wrap it carefully round with hobbies and little luxuries; avoid all entanglements. lock it up safe in the casket or coffin of your selfishness. but in that casket, safe, dark, motionless, airless, it will change. it will not be broken; it will become unbreakable, impenetrable, irredeemable. to love is to be vulnerable." -c.s. lewis #enditmovement❌  #childsextrafficking #edensfarmpgh #volunteer #metoo

text:
◽◽◽◽◽swipe 👈 
please read 👉downed cow: the true story of one anonymous animal born into the meat industry
the truck carrying this cow was unloaded one september morning. after the other animals were removed from the truck, she was left behind, unable to move. the stockyard workers used their customary electric prods in her ear to try to get her to move, then beat and kicked her in the face, ribs, and back but still she couldn't move. they tied a rope around her neck, tied the other end to a post in the ground and drove the truck away. the cow was dragged along the floor of the truck and fell to the ground, landing with both hind legs and her pelvis broken. she remained like that until 7:30 that evening.
_
for the first three hours, she lay in the hot sun crying out. periodically, when she urinated or defecated, she used her front legs to drag herself along the gravel to a clean spot. she also tried to crawl to a shaded area but couldn't move far enough. altogether, she managed to crawl a painful 13 to 14 yards. the stockyard employees wouldn't allow her any drinking water.
_
at 4:30 p.m. three dogs were attacking the cow who was still alive. she had suffered a number of bite wounds. the stockyard workers would not euthanize her, claiming that in order to preserve the value of meat, she could not be destroyed. the butcher eventually arrived at 7:30 p.m. and shot her. her body was purchased for $307.50
_
now you know. the question is what will you do? every bite of animal products that you take involves fear, cruelty, immense suffering, pain and death. ask yourself when you can not only survive but thrive on a plant-based diet, why wouldn't you?
caption #belinda_vegan
➡️www.vegankit.com
➡️www.howdoigovegan.com  video @vegan.remi.2.22
_

text:
pope francis has publicly acknowledged for the first time that there is a problem of priests and even bishops sexually abusing nuns in the roman catholic church. after he was asked to comment on the issue during a news conference aboard a plane returning to rome from a trip to the united arab emirates, the pope admitted that the issue is ongoing and said that they must do more to fight the problem. in recent years, catholic nuns in india, africa, latin america, and italy have accused clerics of sexual abuse, and a vatican magazine last week mentioned nuns having abortions or giving birth to the children of priests, according to the new york times. (📹: reuters)

text:
dream, girl has been hosted by over 350 organizations in 60+ different countries including nasa, starbucks, google, target, twitter, mailchimp, and many more. 
we know diversity and inclusivity are a big part of company culture, but sometimes it's awkward, uncomfortable, or even painful to talk about. which is why our corporate screenings are so powerful.
let the stories in dream, girl do the work for you. listen to the women in the film share how it feels to be underestimated, discriminated against, and what it’s truly like to be a woman in business today.
then after the film, use their stories as a catalyst to open up the conversation and learn about what your company can do to be a more inclusive and inspiring place to work. …
the official dream, girl movie screening package just $99! includes a hard copy of the film on dvd or bluray, your post-screening guidebook to facilitate conversations after the film, marketing materials to help promote your event, a kick-off call with our team, and a listing on our website’s event page.

text:
greta thunberg macht mit ihrem "schulstreik für das klima" weltweit von sich reden. doch sie ist längst nicht die einzige, die für die zukunft ihrer generation kämpft. wir stellen euch drei frauen vor, die eine beeindruckende biographie haben und mit power gegen das "böse auf der welt" vorgehen.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
@nadia_murad_taha hat die gewalt der terrormiliz "is" überlebt, die die volksgruppe der jesiden verfolgte und einen völkermord verübte. murad wurde entführt, gefangen gehalten, gefoltert und vergewaltigt. 5000 menschen fielen der terrororganisation zum opfer. so auch murads mutter und sechs ihrer brüder. die junge frau konnte aus mossul in eine flüchtlingsunterkunft im irak fliehen. 2018 wurde ihr als erste irakerin der friedensnobelpreis verliehen. sie setzt sich bei den vereinten nationen bis heute gegen menschenhandel ein und hat eine eigene initiative für opfer sexueller gewalt.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

text:
red once bled into the painful memories of my past. you can easily lose hope in life when your innocence was taken away at such a young age and when you are continuously reminded that you should have been aborted. the pure rage that was beaten upon my fragile little body revived an inner strength unlike no other. and through it all i still have undying hope for my parents because of the power of forgiveness. faith will do that to you. red. the color of love.

text:
miss mutig via facebook. wir vom feminismus-stammtisch würzburg sind auch vertreten. 
spread the word! teilen erwünscht und kommet in scharen!
"hiermit rufen wir alle feminist_innen, solidarischen männer, queers und freund_innen des freien lebens dazu auf mit uns gegen §218 und §219 und für die freiheit auf die straße zu gehen und zu tanzen!
deutschland im 21. jahrhundert: abtreibungen sind immer noch illegal. 
theoretisch kann mensch dafür bis zu einem jahr eingesperrt werden. wieso gibt es auch jahre nach der ersten großen selbstveröffentlichung von schwangerschaftsabbrüchen diesen diskriminierenden paragraphen immer noch? vor 100 jahren erhielten frauen zum ersten mal das wahlrecht. wieso ist die rechtsprechung dann immer noch nicht bereit, die freie entscheidung über ihr leben und ihren körper an frauen abzugeben? liegt das vielleicht daran, dass im bundestag circa 70% männer sitzen? 
informationen zum thema schwangerschaftsabbruch sind gesellschaftlich kaum verbreitet und junge frauen müssen sich immer noch dafür rechtfertigen, wenn sie sich gegen kinder entscheiden. es hat erst eine starke #metoo bewegung berühmter, reicher frauen und männer gebraucht, damit wieder über non konsensualen sex geredet wird und um das „nein heißt nein“- gesetz zu verabschieden. eine parole die jahrzehnte lang unsere banner zierte und auch heute noch nicht der realität entspricht. 
wenn wir als frauen zusammensitzen und anfangen unsere geschichten zu erzählen, dann werden wir einfach nur wütend. darüber wie unsere gesellschaft uns so stehen lässt, darüber, dass mädchen aller länder auf dem heimweg noch immer angst haben nicht anzukommen. wütend darüber, dass wir noch immer nicht entscheiden können, ob wir unsere leben mit einem kind teilen möchten. wütend über die unsichtbaren geschlechtergrenzen, die uns von ganz klein auf eingetrichtert werden. wütend auf den typen in der bahn, der uns konsequenzlos auf die titten starrt. (...)"

text:
it is a true honor to score for this series of animated shorts for #metoo movement. the videos, which were screened at the sundance film festival 2019. while working on this. by hearing those survivors voices, i can really feel their pain and loneliness. there are so many others in the world needs our support. i'm so grateful that i can do something. we can all do this, support survivors and end sexual violence. 
去年年底替#metoo 做得一系列動畫短片日前在日舞影展(sundance film festival)首映了，配音樂的時候，反覆聽著這些倖存者的獨白，深刻地感受到他們的痛苦與無助。沈默是一種暴力，weinstein事件以後，＃metoo 反性侵及性騷擾社會運動影發熱烈的反響，我才知道原來性侵及性騷擾是如此頻繁而又嚴重被忽視的發生在我們周遭，這些人勇敢的站出來，讓其他倖存者知道他們不需要獨自面對這些傷害。#metoo 不是女權是人權，是對這個社會的公平與正義，我很開心我的音樂能做點什麼。 [story 1 - daniela]  #metoomovement @hornetinc

text:
sometimes we do too!
.
it’s so easy to get overwhelmed and feel like you’ve got too much to do. we often get so caught up thinking about the things we have to do, we end up getting too stressed to do anything! the more we add to our mental list, the more we stress, the less we do, the more the list grows and so on, and so on.
.
so how do you get out of that cycle of overwhelm? <cue thunder and lightning>
.
here’s what i do.
.
first, take a breathe, and write a list of everything you’ve got to get done.  get rid of the mental list. things are a lot less scary when they’re written down.
.
start eliminating the things that aren’t urgent or important. .
then eliminate things that you can ask somebody else to do. contrary to popular belief, you don’t have to do everything yourself! this is a huge bug bear for me because i’m a huge control freak but i have learnt to accept that whilst someone else might not do something exactly the same way i would have, it’s still good enough.
.
pick, at max, 3 most urgent and important things on your list and schedule them in for today. those are the only things you need to get done today!
.
this is probably the hardest and most important step…..
.
focus on one thing at a time.
.
think about nothing other than the task you’re doing until it’s complete. .
this is definitely easier said than done, and it takes practice!!
.
do this for your three tasks and then don’t worry about anything else for the rest of the day!
.
repeat this each day and pretty soon you’ll find that list getting smaller, more manageable and less overwhelming.
.
and whatever you do, don’t bottle it up. just saying to someone who cares, “hey, i’m pretty stressed right now!”, will help to relieve some of that mental strain too.
.
what’s your go-to stress management technique? (wine doesn’t count!)

text:
you are loved! 
you are enough!
you can do hard things!
you have something to offer this world!
you matter!
.
the last two days have been hard! we all have days where our insecurities catch up with us and i have been battling them the last two days. by night time i couldn’t keep the tears at bay. caleb, my 10 year old, was sitting on the kitchen counter brushing his teeth and motioned for me to come over. when i did he just gave me a huge hug. then i really started crying. i told him thanks, i really needed that hug. he asked me what was wrong and i said “do you ever feel like you’re not good enough?” he nodded. i said, “i’m feeling that right now.”
.
when i went to bed there was a note on my pillow. it said:
.
it’s okay. you’re more than good enough, you’re great. and we all love you, even jesus! love caleb!
.
he was like my own little angel last night! his reminder that jesus loves me was like pushing a reset button.
.
sometimes we get caught up in the things we aren’t while failing to notice all the things we are. such a clever tactic by satan! convince us all that we are never enough and he doesn’t even need to do anything else. we’ll tear ourselves up from the inside out! stop listening to his lies!
.
you are loved!
you are enough!
you are beautiful!
you can do hard things!
you have something to offer this world!
you matter!
yes, you!!!!
.
#asoulsurvivorspiritual

text:
tag every man you know who will take this pledge!!!!! when we designed the #protectourgirls by any means necessary tee we also designed another tee.  we didnt release that tee because we were unsure of the words we wanted to say, just that we were certain we wanted men to hold other men accountable in order to affect the change this culture is in desperate need of.  we want to change the narrative of "a girl child ain't safe in a world full of men!" so we waited, and the message came to us via @mrhypeup
*
* “women have been held responsible for the actions of irresponsible, inconsiderate, over-indulgent, entitled, sexually hyperactive men for far too long. it’s time we held men accountable for their behaviour and insist on appropriate autonomy over their thoughts, emotions and actions.

we must challenge society to disrupt the patriarchal ideologies that maintain the understanding that create opportunities for men to pursue immediate sexual gratification by any means necessary." thanks to @mrhypeup for the post.

text: @itsjen.nyc and i went to the opera last night! it was my first time there, the building it extraordinary. would highly rec everyone go, rush tix are $25! we saw don giovanni, good pic for a first opera (legendary, breezy, silly, easy to follow) but truly bizarre in the #metoo era. don is cringy at it's hard to tell if this production wants us to sympathize with him, or understand why he does what he does. tbh i don't understand the character at all, or why this would be staged without consideration for the current climate. very strange. opera, dude!

text:
друзья! на этой неделе вы могли задать свой вопрос заслуженному тренеру россии, тренеру оксаны сливенко - единственной в истории россии олимпийской чемпионки по тяжелой атлетике (2008), тренеру сшор по тяжелой атлетике «мгфсо» москомспорта – владимиру сафонову😎 ⠀
мы отобрали лучшие вопросы на которые ответил владимир🔥:
⠀
❓если сравнить спорт с едой, то с каким блюдом ассоциировалась бы тяжёлая атлетика?😃
⠀
➡️думаю, что бифштекс с кровью. тяжелая пища, как и штанга и кровь не для слабонервных.
⠀
❓ если бы вы не были тренером, то чем хотели бы заняться?
⠀
➡️с детства я интересовался историей. перечитал все возможно доступные книги того времени, ходил в библиотеки, часами сидел в читальных залах и хотел поступить в мгу на исторический факультет.  в 17 лет, выполнив норматив мастера спорта ссср встал вопрос. продолжать занятия спортом, ездить по сборам или поступать в университет? штанга тогда уже заняла своё особое место в моей жизни и я выбрал спорт. иначе мог бы стать преподавателем истории.
⠀
⭕️продолжение в нашей группе вконтакте (ссылка в шапке профиля)
⠀
 #задайвопросчемпиону #владимирсафонов #тяжелаяатлетика #сафонов #супертренер #тренер #спорт #вопросответ #мгфсо #команда_мгфсо #team_mgfso #москва #интервью #чемпион #mgfso #vote #like4like #follow #followme #asmr #fortnite #btsarmy #metoo #timesup #marchforourlives

text:
hi nudies! dear prudence here. i'm in a couple of #metoo conversations with friends atm and it's at once bleak yet filling me with hope. so i thought to extend the discourse to our community.
.

i'd like to reinstate #sundaynvdestalks this sunday with exactly that: an thread of stories of how the #metoo movement has shaped / is shaping our relationships now.
.
we know that the topic can be very triggering for some, so you can opt not to join the convo. it would be a very delicate exchange so we enjoin everyone to maintain the sacredness and safety of our space as we talk about our experiences.
.

text:
peanut, the state's top liberal schnauzer with a long, exalted history of public service, is accused by number of female dogs of unwanted sexual advances.

the revelations came amid a political crisis in virginia. gov. ralph northam and attorney general mark. r. herring said they dressed in blackface decades ago, and lt. gov. justin e. fairfax is accused of sexual assault.

a number of female dogs, among them schnauzers and other breeds, accuse peanut of sexual assault, including many unwanted sexual advances.

a few of the accusers say peanut licked them without consent, and was inappropriately suggestive. “peanut don’t treat his bitches well,” said richmond resident david stanton. “i see him carousing out in the park all the time as if he owns the place and every dog in it.” authorities are investigating the charges, but in the meantime peanut has been prohibited from public spaces.

#blackface #metoo #dog #dogsofinstagram #dogs #virginia #politics #democrats #republicans #scandal #racism #blm

keep the faith! let your faith be bigger than your fear. it’s all about your mindset. everything you do. everything you think. everyone you meet. all of your experiences. how you choose to interpret those experiences. everything is all about your mindset.
it’s the most important part to any person. and it’s completely under your control. it’s completely in your hands. you control what you make of the things and people and places you experience. you control what kind of day you have. you control how you interpret and react to everything that happens around you. you. not anyone else. you.

text:
i've watched the qspiracy since day one.

steve bannon left the wh august 2017 and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences? 'j-c' church militant, anyone?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit a hijacked party is just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt, with the goonsquad known as gop, has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this and messes with the boombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on me me me bed. obviously someone has a lot to lose when none of the us intelligence agencies ends this loonatic travesty.

qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that goebbels would have died for. it is clear that stuff like pizzagate™ was testing and groundwork for the 2016 election and since it proved to be very effective it is used still.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are useless with the content - no way they are going to risk their business by taking responsibility.

there is no way that gop isn't aware of this - after all, cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole narrative is built on the same facebook user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got as cambridge analytica. pedofiles - i bet - but the way things are bundled sure makes goebbels shiver.

trump plays along with his tweets, gestures and words. the bigger issue still - the republicans willingly piggybacked this before the midterms and still keep abusing the faith of their fellow men.

this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

text:
my healing process involves a lot of writing.

growing up in a culture that undervalues intuition and subtle senses, not learning how to claim them for myself, it was easy to push down and ignore feelings, to sing them aside for what my culture told me would prove my worth.

like a relationship. even one that i knew from the beginning didn't feel right. my mind could easily find ways to convince me to stay, that the only worth i would find as a woman would be wrapped up in a man's arms.

my healing process involves writing my feelings. my anger, confusion, sadness and regret. validating those feelings and making them real.

my healing process also involves pouring through old journals, seeking to understand myself, to remember the feelings and dreams that got lost under trauma recycled into another relationship.

as i was reading last night, i decided there is a lot i want to share. i want to make it all real for me again, so that i can find strength in my senses to not let them slip past my awareness again.

my story is not linear, and i do not intend to tell it as such, but it will flow as follows. "he took advantage of me. he saw in me something that he wanted, and he did whatever he could to take it. he lied, manipulated, sweet talked, and controlled the situation to have me dropping my boundaries, my faith, and my gut instincts so that i'd let him in.

so he took me, and i was too confused to say no. i surrendered, in a twisted way, to his will and i let myself be pulled into his grasp. he claimed my body because i hadn't, and couldn't.

satisfied with his fill, he released his hold enough for me to feel my skin, raw from his touch. i felt my heart, wounded by betrayal, and i sank into a river of tears for the violation to my spirit.

my eyes burned with the pain of losing sight of my power - seeing only how i'd let my body be used for his gain. i felt weak for the self-sacrifice, feeling that truly i was nothing more than property for him to set his sights on to conquer and own.

my value for my own worth was reflected clearly, and i took it as a sign of truth, rather than seeing it for the hateful love that it was." ~rhea heartsong~
feb 5/19

text:
wylie, who worked for scl, the british-based parent of cambridge analytica, told the senate judiciary committee that cambridge analytica hired hackers to collect data it then used against opponents of its political clients.

allegations of the improper use of data for 87 million facebook users by cambridge analytica, which was hired by trump's 2016 election campaign, have led to investigations in the united states and europe.

bannon worked on trump's campaign and became a white house aide when trump took office in january 2017. bannon left in august 2017.

wylie, who has provided reports about how the firm used data facebook collected, on wednesday described discussions at the company about suppressing the vote, exploiting racial tensions, and testing campaign slogans in 2014 for use in the 2016 election.
.
- one of the things that did provoke me to leave was the beginnings of discussions of voter disengagement, i have seen documents reference and i recall conversations that it was intended to focus on african-american voters, wylie said. - the company learned that there were segments of the population that responded to messages like 'drain the swamp' or images of border walls or indeed paranoia about the 'deep state' that weren't necessarily reflected in mainstream polling or mainstream political discourse that steve bannon was interested in to help build his movement, wylie said.

another witness who testified to the judiciary committee, tufts university associate professor eitan hersh, said he was "skeptical" of the effectiveness that such political messaging and targeting. - no person is persuadable all the time, he said.

mark hosenball
reuters

text:
#refecttorenew #day 5 guided #writing @weareselfcentered
✍🏾embarrassing to admit, at 29 most of my life has felt like a major struggle just to have an equitable and enjoyable quality of life experience. from being bullied/terrorized for the entirety of grade school until graduation, to being adopted, to dealing with parents’ divorce, to having to work from the age of 14–through college and graduate education, to a list of failed, toxic relationships. on many days, i have found myself weary from the weight and burdens of significant trauma. i can feel my body shrink and cave in under the pressure.
to relieve myself from this feeling the quickest healing is to breathe deeply and slowly
🧘🏾‍♀️ my herstory is one of the reasons i am firmly committed to doing the spiritual self-development work necessary to permanently shift outdated paradigms and reboot my brain to manifest ease, joy, abundance, love, and success. 👍🏽
one recent challenge i have overcome is navigating a series of mini-housing crises since a #metoo incident in 2012 radically changed my life course. this saga lasted over 8 years and sent my life journey down a vastly different trajectory than the perfect picture i had once envisioned. an abusive ivy-league ex boyfriend cheated on me multiple times and his encore presentation...was to set me up to be sexually assaulted and humiliated in front of him by the woman he played me with. both of them admitted (at the time of the incident) to the situation being premeditated and planned in advance by them. this situation spiraled further out of control when that same ex came to my apartment in santa monica, ca around the thanksgiving break holiday to attempt to apologize and repair our relationship. 🙅🏾‍♀️
the incident ended with an ivy-league educated man attempting to hit me with his car, the police arriving threatening to take only me to jail, since he was long gone by the time they arrived, me experiencing muteness and an inability to speak and express for about 1.5 months, and “a series of unfortunate events” in multitude afterwards. this ushered shame in my life because it directly impacted my financial well-being and my brain continue-in comments 👉

memories: 2001 found this little gem cleaning out my art studio yesterday. i think it’s ok to look back and see what was with wiser eyes. important though, to look gently and with a heart full of love. see what was with acceptance, and maybe be open to new insights. i see my children now, from a distance…i see how little, gentle and delicate they were, but surprisingly too, i see how vulnerable i was. how much i wanted support, to feel love and to be seen. i’m glad i didn’t know then the immense struggles i would have - but to name them here and now - would be to call them back to me. by knowing what was/is true and standing in the light, i have survived and thrived ... and so have they. 
as i have been finding my way to finally being comfortable in my own skin, they are naturally blossoming into brilliant, creative, authentic people. so much pride. so much love...for us all. 💛💜❤️
#onelove #mothers #metoo #innerintegration #narcissisticabuse #ancestors #legacy 
#traumarecovery #posttraumaticgrowth #sacredfeminine #goddess #divinefeminine

text:
trapped emotions
pain, anger, humiliation, control, shame, isolation — all heightened by withholding information. holding your emotions inside you hoping it will protect you but it just comes off in other forms of self harm, outbursts and personal entrapment.
h e a l i n g - the first way to heal is to acknowledge that there is a problem. after spending so much time being brave, it feels threatening to let your guard down. start slowly, start somewhere. begin releasing your grip on your trauma
#journeytolight

text:
on episode 75 of @americansexpodcast sunny & @dirtylola's reflection on the surviving r. kelly docuseries leads to an impromptu conversation about america’s long history of sexualizing teens. we’re all shocked by the r. kelly story but remember back in high school when it was “cool” to date a college-aged person? remember when adults in your life didn’t bat an eye at you dating a legal adult when you were underage? we break this complicated situation down by reflecting on our own experiences. some of what we touched on: hitting puberty early, the over-sexualization of girls of color, how being sexually objectified as a teen shapes one’s sexuality, mary kay letourneau, the negative impacts of marrying young, the cultural normalization of teens dating adults, equating sex with love, why people stay in abusive situations & more. you also get a sneak peek of our @patreon #shoottheshit bonus episodes. °
°
get the episode here: http://sunnymegatron.com/surviving-r-kelly-podcast/ (link in bio)

on episode 75 of @americansexpodcast sunny & @dirtylola's reflection on the surviving r. kelly docuseries leads to an impromptu conversation about america’s long history of sexualizing teens. we’re all shocked by the r. kelly story but remember back in high school when it was “cool” to date a college-aged person? remember when adults in your life didn’t bat an eye at you dating a legal adult when you were underage? we break this complicated situation down by reflecting on our own experiences. some of what we touched on: hitting puberty early, the over-sexualization of girls of color, how being sexually objectified as a teen shapes one’s sexuality, mary kay letourneau, the negative impacts of marrying young, the cultural normalization of teens dating adults, equating sex with love, why people stay in abusive situations & more. you also get a sneak peek of our @patreon #shoottheshit bonus episodes. °

i am looking for participants to get involved with this work, if you feel comfortable talking about your experiences please message me through private messages, you will remain anonymous. this comment was said by artist chuck close after being accused of sexual harassment from several women.

text:
[ focus ] 1/2 • maurice et les droits des femmes • (ancienne colonie anglaise indépendante depuis 1968 et membre du commonwealth depuis 1992) •
👉c’est en 1835 suite à l’abolition de l’esclavage, que les habitants eurent leurs premiers droits. mais ce n’est que plus tard que ces droits progressèrent sur la voie de l’égalité. auparavant, à maurice, comme ailleurs, le rôle de la femme ne consistait qu’en une présence importante au sein de la famille et dans la religion. 👉 depuis, les choses ont évolué. la femme a obtenu des droits en commençant par le droit de vote accordé en 1948. 📍 mais les plus nombreux sont les droits sociaux : le droit à l’éducation, au travail, au logement, ou encore à d’autres droits plus récents comme le droit à l’avortement, légalisé en mai 2012 mais applicable sous certaines conditions : en cas d'inceste, de viol, de malformation du fœtus, ou de danger pour la mère. les femmes souhaitant avorter, mais ne remplissant pas les conditions définies par la loi, doivent trouver des moyens hors du cadre légal. un commerce illégal est donc apparu avec de graves conséquences sur la santé des femmes. 👉le gouvernement a établit des mesures drastiques telle que la « convention sur l’élimination de toutes les formes de discriminations à l’égard des femmes » en 1979. 👉les « restriction orders », lois contre la violence domestique, a aussi conduit à la création d’un amendement pour la protection de la femme qui est le « protection from domestic violence (amndment) act » créé en 2007. mais les mentalités restent difficiles à changer...
📍et #metoo n'a par ailleurs pas connu un grand retentissement sur l'île. "maurice étant un petit pays, les victimes ont peur d’être blacklistées" expliquait diksha beehary, avocate et présidente de mafubo mauritius, association qui milite pour les droits de la femme.
👉on note pourtant certaines avancées comme en politique avec des femmes candidates et ministres. mais également avec une femme présidente, de 2016 à 2018, ameenah gurib-fakim, et la présidente de l'assemblée nationale maya hanoomanjee depuis 2014.
•
#lesambitieuses #borntobeambitious #women #maurice

text:
#metoo: accusing repeatedly without formal complaint is not authentic, says kailash kher
#
mumbai: singer kailash kher, who has been accused by multiple women of sexual harassment, says that in his view, if a person is not making a formal complaint and just continues to accuse, it is not authentic. kailash was interacting with the media at the music launch of marathi film "dokyala shot" along with riteish deshmukh and abhijit panse here. a few months ago, singer sona mahapatra had shared her alleged unsavoury experience with kailash, and after that, at least four other women raised allegations against the "teri deewani" singer. sona, in an interview, has said she will not lodge a police complaint against kailash, but she will make sure he doesn't repeat his alleged act in future. kailash kherreacting to this, kailash said: "everyone has their own thinking. if i accuse someone only by taking that individual's name over and over again then, nothing will come out of it. if you will take legal recourse against that person, then it becomes another matter altogether. "if i tell you that i will not make a complaint against that individual, but still i will accuse him of doing certain criminal activity, then i feel it's not an authentic complaint." does he…

text:
pope francis has publicly acknowledged for the first time that there is a problem of priests and even bishops sexually abusing nuns in the roman catholic church. after he was asked to comment on the issue during a news conference aboard a plane returning to rome from a trip to the united arab emirates, the pope admitted that the issue is ongoing and said that they must do more to fight the problem. in recent years, catholic nuns in india, africa, latin america, and italy have accused clerics of sexual abuse, and a vatican magazine last week mentioned nuns having abortions or giving birth to the children of priests, according to the new york times. (📹: reuters)

text:
yo te creo. es increíble por todo lo que tienen que pasar las mujeres en todos los ámbitos de su vida. y como hombre, además de condenar la actitud de esos hombres que se han aprovechado de su posición, fama y poder, me pongo a pensar precisamente en eso, en el por qué lo hicieron. más que un mensaje de apoyo a las mujeres, (no significa que no lo esté haciendo) es un mensaje a todos. ¿qué nos pasa cuando nos sentimos en el poder de hacer algo? es decir, en el caso de oscar arias, él hizo lo que hizo porque es una figura importantísima nacional e internacionalmente y eso, en su mente, le da el poder de cruzar barreras que nosotros los mortales no podemos. ahora, sí, el mae se equivocó y que pase lo que tenga que pasar con él, pero el problema viene desde abajo. ¿por qué los corruptos roban tanto? porque pueden y están en la posición de hacerlo. yo una vez tuve el poder de regalar un premio de una rifa y se lo di a un amigo, ¿por qué? porque estaba en la posición de hacerlo, aún sabiendo que no debía. a esto voy, este asunto tiene muchas formas de ser analizado. además de reprochar el acoso sexual que viven diariamente las mujeres, hay que entender qué si hacemos cosas que no debemos y nos aprovechamos de algunas situaciones, ¿qué no haríamos si tuviéramos la posición que tienen estas personas que están siendo acusadas? todo comienza desde abajo. .
.
.

text:
💖la belleza de anna nos comparte su historia💖: desde muy pequeña he cargado con una oscuridad infinita, es realmente fría y no entendía que era hasta que en mí adolescencia me la presentaron como depresión crónica, jamás me la traté, pero vaya que ella me trató a mí.

me hizo conocer el frío que hace en unos brazos vacíos y sin consuelo, hasta que a punto de perder mi vida vi una luz y me aferré a ella. me costó, a quien lleva tantos años encerrado le cuesta saber cuándo es libre, pero cuando lo sentí, cuando mi mente empezó a dejar filtrar ese calor en mí, me di cuenta de lo que valgo. hay condenas más largas, más violentas y desesperantes, pero todas al final nos enseñan que para salvarnos no necesitamos a otros, nos necesitamos a nosotros. 🌿💖💕
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.

text:
it has been more than two years since former fox news host gretchen carlson settled her sexual harassment lawsuit against the channel’s ex-ceo roger ailes for $20 million, and now, she is helping other women tell their raw and real stories of harassment in the workplace. carlson opens up to salon about how she's trying to get answers for others, including calling out the companies who are failing them — like mcdonald's — and why men are key to dismantling the tangled web of on-the-job abuse. carlson goes on the road and meets women across the country who are dealing with the fallout from reporting sexual harassment to their employers in her new documentary, "gretchen carlson: breaking the silence," available on lifetime. but the former fox news host made sure "to feature more of the every woman's story instead of just famous hollywood actor's stories,” she said on a recent episode of "salon talks." to watch the full episode, click the link in bio.
—

text:
got a super interesting response in my inbox yesterday... 😳
.
.
if you watch my stories, you saw that i shared something that was on my heart about women.
. .
there’s such a big movement right now of women rights, women’s equality and so on. yet, it seems that women are the first to judge, tear down or even bully other women any chance they get.
.
.
how do we expect to set a new standard for the way women are viewed if we, as women are not setting the example of what acceptance and empowerment looks like??? 🧐
.
.
i think we, as women can improve. it is harder than ever to put yourself out there, be vulnerable and share your authentic self. so together, we should encourage, love, support and cheer other women on for being their true selves! 🚺
.
.
am i right? yes or yes? 😬🙏🏼✨ .
.

text:
i constantly remind myself how strong my emotions can be. perhaps what i label as love is something else, something so sinister and powerful that everytime it leaves, it turns my life upside down. so sometimes i tell myself, i will stay quiet. i will confine myself to the four walls in my room. i will look out the window when people talk. i will shut myself up when i feel. i will not listen to my heart. whenever i feel the need to be loved and known, i will do the opposite of what gets me there. when i'm in love i will treat it with indifference until it dries, its roots, and dies a ghostly death. 
i will make myself invisible.
name: Writings Of An Unstable Mind

text:

it took me till 38 years old to get here but the view is priceless. sober and debt free, i believed it was impossible but here i am.

a dream come true
in malibu

text:
calling all girls and women! 
be in control of your personal safety! 
would you like the skill and knowledge to know what to do and how to react if faced with an aggressor? 
to feel safe and confident when travelling, going out or with a young child. 
this course will help you take those steps. taught by someone who had to take them herself. 
this is self defence course specifically designed to tackle the types of violent situations women and girls are like to face. 
learn how to use what you have to your advantage. “overcoming fear is one of the biggest struggles even for women who train, this is one of the topics we will be covering. we want to ensure the women who attend leave equipped with strong mental attitude and how to tune into their own ability to survive as well as a physical skill set” sifu della 
physical, mental and internal training is what our course is offering. 
sifu della knows first hand how frightening and disabling it can be to face a dangerous person who can very easily overpower you. 
she will be sharing her experience and has written the program based on that understanding and her years of training martial arts and self empowerment. 
offering 5 free spaces to women who are experiencing or have experiences some form of harassment or violence in their lives! inbox to secure place. 
link in bio to book for the course

text:
truth!
♡
if we really want to love we must learn how to forgive.
♡
that includes forgiving others, even for the unthinkable, and forgiving ourselves, even for the unthinkable!
♡
it’s not always easy to forgive.
♡
when my coach gave me an assignment to write a letter to the person that repeatedly sexually abused my body and find compassion for him i felt a lot of resistance inside because i really didn’t want to do the assignment. (i didn’t have to mail it or give it to him. i just needed to write it.) but i was paying her to coach me and push me out of my comfort zone. i reminded myself of a mantra that struck a chord with me when i heard tony robbins at one of his seminars belt it out in his deep commanding voice: “if you can’t, you must”, so i begrudgingly started writing.
♡
that letter was just the start of the forgiveness process for me. it wasn’t until two years later and after i completed numerous intense therapy sessions, cried an abundance of tears, and experienced countless ah-ha’s, that i was ready to genuinely forgive him. not because someone told me to, not because that’s what i was supposed to do, but because i was ready to let go. ♡
forgiveness is a process, and we must learn it if we really want to love.
.
.
.
.
.
#learnhowtoforgive #motherteresa#forgivnessheals #forgivenessisaprocess #metoo #metoomovement #othersideofmetoo #tonyrobbins #ifyoucantyoumust

text:
‘you better love loving and you better behave’ tears for fears 1989 .
.
i saw them play at the 02 last night. can a band get more relevant as time passes? ‘woman in chains’ has to be one of their best tracks. so relevant today as it was in 1989. a testament to how far women still need to go to gain equality! i worked on the record counter at woolworths in 1989 and every chance i got i played their album ‘the seeds of love’, and often got told off for playing it too loud. i absolutely love that album. if you want relevant, music 🎧 with purpose check out their greatest hits album from 2017. bravo for last night @tearsforfearsmusic excellent show.  and alison moyet you rocked! @alisonmoyetofficial .
.
#pressforprogress #womaninchains #wearefuturefemale #metoo #metoomovement #timesup #callitout #love #everydaysexism #habitualsexism #tearsforfears #alisonmoyetlive

text:
wylie, who worked for scl, the british-based parent of cambridge analytica, told the senate judiciary committee that cambridge analytica hired hackers to collect data it then used against opponents of its political clients.

allegations of the improper use of data for 87 million facebook users by cambridge analytica, which was hired by trump's 2016 election campaign, have led to investigations in the united states and europe.

bannon worked on trump's campaign and became a white house aide when trump took office in january 2017. bannon left in august 2017.

wylie, who has provided reports about how the firm used data facebook collected, on wednesday described discussions at the company about suppressing the vote, exploiting racial tensions, and testing campaign slogans in 2014 for use in the 2016 election.
.
- one of the things that did provoke me to leave was the beginnings of discussions of voter disengagement, i have seen documents reference and i recall conversations that it was intended to focus on african-american voters, wylie said. - the company learned that there were segments of the population that responded to messages like 'drain the swamp' or images of border walls or indeed paranoia about the 'deep state' that weren't necessarily reflected in mainstream polling or mainstream political discourse that steve bannon was interested in to help build his movement, wylie said.

another witness who testified to the judiciary committee, tufts university associate professor eitan hersh, said he was "skeptical" of the effectiveness that such political messaging and targeting. - no person is persuadable all the time, he said.

mark hosenball
reuters

text:
ever feel like your kids are your shadows? 
maybe it’s all the snow we are getting or that we are just in the midst of winter, but lately my kids want to be involved in everything i’m doing. (i’m even admitting we all go to the potty together 😜) these past few nights i’ve been getting so frustrated because simple tasks like making dinner or starting laundry is taking 3x as long because my little ones need me, want to help l, and ‘do what i do.’ well, guess what, emily this is a huge opportunity to teach them and then have them learn.  yeah, took me a bit to figure this one out,  but simple things like prepping food or putting soap in the washing is a really big deal to these little minds.  i mean, stop to think about the last time you learned something new and how fun it was ... this is their every day!!! #wintertime #toddleractivities #learning #teaching #momtip #metoo #mommyslittlehelper

text:
u.s. president donald trump's former aide steve bannon sought to use personal information collected online to promote "a culture war," a whistleblower on now-defunct political data firm cambridge analytica told u.s. senators on wednesday.

bannon, a former cambridge analytica vice president, "saw cultural warfare as a means to create enduring change in american politics," testified christopher wylie, who says information about tens of millions of facebook users ended up in cambridge analytica's hands.

bannon's attorney william burck did not immediately respond to an email request for comment on wylie's testimony.

wylie, who worked for scl, the british-based parent of cambridge analytica, told the senate judiciary committee that cambridge analytica hired hackers to collect data it then used against opponents of its political clients.

allegations of the improper use of data for 87 million facebook users by cambridge analytica, which was hired by trump's 2016 election campaign, have led to investigations in the united states and europe.

mark hosenball
reuters

text:
i did what i had to do to survive. as i healed from abuse in seeking what i thought was self care i taught myself to indulge myself with food and reward myself with unhealthy behaviour. as a woman i was taught to put everyone first before myself. however this did not help this just taught me to internalize and neglect myself. . 
years of therapy taught me that i could take time to myself. that i needed to start saying no if did not serve me or my family first. last year was a big year of healing for me. first came my emotional and spiritual self. my learning to treat myself how i deserved to be treated. after came the residual hurt that had manifested in my body and every symptom that pointed to fibromyalgia had me defeated. i refused to believe that was what the rest of my life would look. i truly learned that: "self-care is not an indulgence. self-care is a discipline. it requires tough-mindedness, a deep and personal understanding of your priorities, and a respect for both yourself and the people you choose to spend your life with." https://bit.ly/2uokpux
.
i decided it was time to really care for myself and started by focusing on my nutrition and my bathroom cabinet went from 6rx to help me deal and cope with ptsd to a vitalizing plan. i was used to the side effects the anxiety, depression and pain medication had given me. i accepted them as being normal. so when the vitalizer plan started to renew my body i was not sure what to do with all the well being that it brought me. after taking those rx for about 7 years, i find myself grateful to to go to bed and not have to take my meds. vitalizing plan and self care has heal me from anxiety, depression, and i dare to say fibromyalgia!
.
whatever you do take time for yourself today, read a book, mediate. just say no to what others are asking you to do and do something just for yourself! .

.
today is #shinealightonslavery day and i don’t know about you but i was shocked when i heard that statistic. abraham lincoln didn’t abolish slavery- he just abolished it being about race. today there are more women, men, and children of all different races and ethnicities in modern day slavery. ever heard of the #metoo movement? that’s another awareness movement to get the word out about the seriousness of sex slavery. while there are more people in slavery today than every before we have also never been close to ending slavery once and for all. because today slavery is illegal everywhere- all over the world. slavery is illegal. together we can end the fight. show me your red x’s and join me in the #enditmovement ❌

text:
as part of sexual violence awareness week we went into the cabinet office to talk about what we can do to eradicate gender based violence. ✊🏻✊🏼✊🏽✊🏾✊🏿
.
we sat down and talked about the importance of community, collaboration and storytelling as a way to generate real change, and open up the discussion on abuse. .
we were so inspired and excited by the wonderful people we were talking to we forgot to take any pictures, but we thought this quote by maya angelou is pretty fitting. .
by going into the cabinet office today we were able to start a conversation, in a space that has the power to create change. every story matters. every voice matters. no matter how big or small your platform is, every small conversation helps to create a tidal wave that people can no longer ignore. #metoo is proof of that. it is time we believe survivors and work together in whatever capacity we can to end abuse. .
✏️ @kimothy.joy .
.
.

.
.

text:
19 hours ago @sarahkatesilverman shared her story of inappropriate touch by a medical professional. thank you for bringing awareness. although wildly triggering, it needs to be heard. it needs to be repeated. reading the vulnerability in this post by a grown woman with a voice vs remembering the voiceless vulnerability of being in this position, repeatedly, as a child is heart shattering.
...
the internal screams persist throughout life. some of us will scream externally & still will not be heard. this is not an anomaly. this is too common. this is an #intersectional issue spanning all cultures, ethnicities, & socioeconomic backgrounds. regarding medical visits: there should always be a second professional or female with you. no one should be handling you ungloved. you have every right to request a different, or specific practitioner. ...
those of you in authority, please stop abusing the vulnerable. let us live our lives in beauty & wonder rather than traumatic memories & fear. ...
#pedophilepediatrician #metoo #kids2 #kidstoo #nypasscva #intersectional #whyididntreport

text_retweet:
repost @healthforourbabies tmrw marks 1 year that we went to hayden’s pediatrician and she received her mmr vaccine. not a clue of the poison that was circulating her little one year old body, injuring her developing brain + causing 6th nerve palsy. you can listen to her vaccine injury story on our podcast, epi #6 (link above). please share her story with another mom who’s thinking of vaccinating her babies. ⁣⁣⁣
3 things:⁣⁣⁣
1. words can never express how incredibly thankful i am to all your beautiful heartfelt prayers. you downloading her podcast story, sharing it with friends has really helped spread awareness—it’s the most downloaded episode. ⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
2. what a blessing it is to see her recovery, it’s night + day! we recently went to a vision therapist who stated they couldn’t do any therapy until she was at least 4 years old. however, the risk of waiting this long is her injured right eye will think this is the new normal potentially causing the eye to permanently stay that way. so in the meantime, we’re doing the natural approach: eye patch, glasses, cod oil, vit c, eo’s + camu camu. we’ve seen a drastic improvement in her vision in the last month bc of camu camu so thank you for the referral!⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
3. i am still heartbroken that our world hasn’t woken up to the dangers of vaccines. how is this worldwide epidemic that is injuring and killing our children not national + international news? how is it that 70 dangerous vaccines that have to be given to our children including flu shots (or our kids can’t go to school) being mandated by our govt? how is it that vaccines which have little to no studies being created by pharma, approved by the cdc, placed into the hands of doctors, then injected into our precious perfect babies not alarming to every human on earth? how is this not going viral and demanding change like the #metoo or the women empowerment movement? if we don’t demand change from our govt to stop pharma + cdc, then we will continue to have generations of unhealthy children with cancer, allergies, autoimmune diseases, neurological damage, esotropia, sids (a cover up btw) + the list goes on. all for the sake of money and greed. we demand change ❤️

text:
first things first, i’m okay.. i’m not in a dark place right now. but there will never be a right time to post this. i won’t delve too far into it. i will let you know this: this is truly a personal experience and i’ve struggled to come to terms with this over the years. i’ve struggled to admit that it happened. i still do but it did. and i live with it and i grow and evolve from it. i put on a brave face but i’m still scared. nowadays, i’ll be perfectly fine, living the best life possible. but that’s not always the case for everyone. i’m in a better place now, although there will be times where the memories will randomly hit me. 
sexual violence victims/sufferers should not have to feel alone or feel ashamed. the purpose of #metoo is to #empower women and men, who are victims of #sexualharrassment and violence, through #empathy. the #purpose is to give #courage and #strength to stand up and face your attacker. the #metoomovement is to let you know that you do not have to fight this on your own. 
lastly, only a couple people closest to me know about it. this isn’t something that i told everyone, even though it is about to be known to whoever is reading this. i don’t want any of you to worry or wonder but be educated in a way. you or someone you know has experienced sexual harassment/violence. 
#personal #confession #words #poetry

text:
before you released lust for life in 2017, you released a trailerfor the album, and you talked about how the music was a reflection of transitioning from one era to another. was it any different this time around? did you feel like you were still in that transitional period, or in a completely different space?

ldr: "yes and no. i think my biggest surprise is that i expected to feel like i was out of that transition. we're a couple years into the presidency and a couple of years into some of the cultural and political destruction we've all been experiencing. #metoo is a year and a half old. we've got a lot of [huge changes]. i think i'm always expecting to wake up at the beginning of january and feel like a brand new person, and the same with the record. i'm always expecting to be the next version of myself by the time i'm done.
actually i am feeling like there has been a continued shift throughout this record, but not in the way i thought it would be. i think i wait for this "aha" moment to dawn upon me, and things don't really work like that. growth doesn't always happen in a straight line. it's not like you wake up one day, and you're like, "now i'm gonna do disco!" and i'm a new genre. it's more like, progress is back and forth and i think it's just having the willingness to want, for me. my goal is for things to be really safe and serene and fun, just in my own personal life and in my music. for my music, my aspirations are for things to get deeper and smarter, and if the melodies can still be beautiful then that's a cherry on top for sure. they all of go hand-in-hand. they all sort of happen at the same time."

before you released lust for life in 2017, you released a trailerfor the album, and you talked about how the music was a reflection of transitioning from one era to another. was it any different this time around? did you feel like you were still in that transitional period, or in a completely different space?

ldr: "yes and no. i think my biggest surprise is that i expected to feel like i was out of that transition. we're a couple years into the presidency and a couple of years into some of the cultural and political destruction we've all been experiencing.  is a year and a half old. we've got a lot of [huge changes]. i think i am always expecting to wake up at the beginning of january and feel like a brand new person, and the same with the record. i am always expecting to be the next version of myself by the time i am done.
actually i am feeling like there has been a continued shift throughout this record, but not in the way i thought it would be. i think i wait for this "aha" moment to dawn upon me, and things do not really work like that. growth does not always happen in a straight line. it is not like you wake up one day, and you are like, "now i am gonna do disco!" and i am a new genre. it is more like, progress is back and foh and i think it is just having the willingness to want, for me. my goal is for things to be really safe and serene and fun, just in my own personal life and in my music. for my music, my aspirations are for things to get deeper and smaer, and if the melodies can still be beautiful then that's a cherry on top for sure. they all of go hand-in-hand. they all so of happen at the same time."
lana for harper'sbazaar -

text:
ikväll var det releasefest  för min fina fina vän och psykologkollega calle brunells bok ”man - i ljuset av #metoo”.
boken berör vad som hände med män efter #metoo, när alla berättelser kom så nära. från en syster, vän, flickvän eller mamma. då blev det plötsligt verkligt. män började fråga sig: vad har jag för ansvar som man? hur kan jag bidra till förändring?
(calle läste ett stycke om när han hållit i ett samtal om sex och sexualitet med de intagna på ett fängelse och hur den finska jarmo helt tog över samtalet. bara det lilla gjorde mig extremt peppad på att läsa mer!)
grattis honey! 💖@callebrunell @brombergsforlag 
#mansrollen #maskulinitetsnormer #metoo

for those that missed it, please join us for our upcoming programs in san francisco march 19th and 21st.

reposted from @torontocowsave -  women, mothers, feminists: did you know about this? - #februdairyfree day 3

whether it's an industrial #dairy farm or a small scale, organic farm, the process to produce #breastmilk is the same: a young female #cow is continually, artificially, and forcefully inseminated to produce a calf who is then torn away from her shortly after birth so that her milk can be sold to humans instead. when she can no longer keep up with the quantity of #milk demand placed on her, she will be slaughtered (at a fraction of her natural life-span) and ground into low-grade #hamburger.
💔🐮💔

-
-

text:
se viene un nuevo paro de mujeres. un nuevo evento donde el feminismo nacional se concentra para perder el tiempo. pensando que esta luchando por un patriarcado que se va caer mediante repetir slogans como un coro de loros. 
mas alla que estos eventos me parecen una estupidez porque al final del dia, tenes a la izquierda y progresia (que tambien participan en estas marchas) votando a favor de violadores y delincuentes.

da tristeza la cantidad de gente que manipulan y que piensan que son revolucionarios cuando son mas que nada lo mismo que un fanatico religioso, solo que en vez de satanas, se la agarran con el patriarcado.

en fin, sean funcionales chicas, total ya nos acostumbrarnos a fumarnos su frustración de no hacer nada y que todo empeore. .

si bien bryan singer rechazó las acusaciones, bafta mantendrá la medida hasta que sean resueltas en un juicio.

madrid.- la academia británica de las artes cinematográficas y de la televisión suspendió la nominación de bryan singer por su trabajo en "bohemian rhapsody", luego de las múltiples acusaciones de presunta agresión y abuso sexual a varias mujeres, entre ellas, una menor de 17 años.
