text:
i actually do receive a good amount of messages from men wishing that "male issues" would be addressed more in the news or on social media.
however, i see this topic significantly different. i don’t believe the answer as a women is addressing male issues head on, it turns away a vast amount of women from listening.
instead, i believe it is more important to highlight the rights we as women have that men do not.
why? 
because i believe the reason we have any of today’s issues and this new hatred for "toxic masculinity" entirely falls on feminism.
since the start of today’s version of feminism the claim has been that they are fighting for "equal rights for women."
truth is, it is merely nothing more than a targeted ploy to destroy men which results in the issues we have today.
.
to push against third wave feminism, we as women must prove to other women that we already have more rights & privileges than men in effort to halt or prevent a further spreading of todays current hatred or inequality.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.

text:
thursday thoughts 💭

a staggering 98% of music industry producers are men and 97% of music industry engineers/mixers are men. lets get #womeninthemix. so when people say that the music industry is male dominated, it definately comes from somewhere! 
patriarchal culture is still real across the music industry and the #metoo movement has clarified that some women have been targeted by these men due to their positions and misogyny, causing a hierarchical stature in the industry where this power has been abused.

this has occured in different ways stemming from a lack of respect towards female co-workers, from women earning less and feeling unheard, to cases of sexual assault and harassment, where unfortunately the perpetrators in power have managed to maintain their jobs. thanks to #metoo, some women have begun to find liberation from these situations but others are still fighting hard to make changes in the scene.

more men need to become aware of the reality of this and invite, introduce and welcome more women into the music industry with open arms and a supportive nature. some women may even feel intimidated by such figures or feel belittled by some. no matter which gender you identify with, we must empower one another to all get involved in the industry to succeed, regardless of statistics and gender politics.

this would help make permanent positive changes in the music industry and the world we live in by causing awareness. let’s achieve this by supporting one another in order to provide equal opportunities within the music industry and by providing a healthy workplace for all future workers! ⭐️
:
 #womeninthemix #femaledjs #femaleproducers #womenartists #womeninmusic #musicindustry #statistics #patriarchy #contemporarymusic #furiousfemmes #artcollective #raisingawareness #musicengineering #femalemusicians #thursdaythoughts #londonartists
name: FURIOUS FEMMES COLLECTIVE
tweet_full:
thursday thoughts 💭

a staggering 98% of music industry producers are men and 97% of music industry engineers/mixers are men. lets get #womeninthemix. so when people say that the music industry is male dominated, it definately comes from somewhere! 
patriarchal culture is still real across the music industry and the #metoo movement has clarified that some women have been targeted by these men due to their positions and misogyny, causing a hierarchical stature in the industry where this power has been abused.

this has occured in different ways stemming from a lack of respect towards female co-workers, from women earning less and feeling unheard, to cases of sexual assault and harassment, where unfortunately the perpetrators in power have managed to maintain their jobs. thanks to #metoo, some women have begun to find liberation from these situations but others are still fighting hard to make changes in the scene.

more men need to become aware of the reality of this and invite, introduce and welcome more women into the music industry with open arms and a supportive nature. some women may even feel intimidated by such figures or feel belittled by some. no matter which gender you identify with, we must empower one another to all get involved in the industry to succeed, regardless of statistics and gender politics.

this would help make permanent positive changes in the music industry and the world we live in by causing awareness. let’s achieve this by supporting one another in order to provide equal opportunities within the music industry and by providing a healthy workplace for all future workers! ⭐️
:

text_retweet:
#repost @britt.lit28 (@get_repost)
・・・
my best friend's cousin was gang raped this past december in bolivia. this is her post. please consider posting a picture of yourself with these hashtags. sexual violence against women is an epidemic across the globe, and with the #metoo movement and as we continue to listen to and support and #believesurvivors please let us extend this compassion & love & passion for change across borders. ·
**michelle's post**
·  this past december my 18 year old cousin was drugged, beaten, and gang raped. since then, there has been an effort by the families of the abusers to discredit my cousin, destroy evidence, and make this issue disappear. my family does not want her to be just another victim of sexual violence whose plea for justice goes unheard. sexual violence and violence against women are issues that have been ignored for far too long, both in the us and abroad. bolivia has the highest rates of sexual violence in latin america, with 1 in 3 women experiencing some form of sexual violence before the age of 18. it is time to listen, to take action, and to believe women. we, alongside women’s rights advocacy groups in bolivia, hope that by using these hashtags we are able to increase awareness of this issue and persuade the authorities to do what is right and just. if you are able and want to participate, please take a picture of yourself with the these hashtags and post to social media: #yositecreo #carcelalatropa #usa. the hashtags mean “i believe you,” and “jail for the gang” (technically troop, but referring to the group of men that raped her) 
thank you. 
michelle & the family of the survivor
todos te creemos

#yositecreo #carcelalatropa #usa

"a hard question that needs to be asked:⠀
⠀
hetero ladies: do you care about consent and want the men in your life to always respect your boundaries? and: do you also find it unsexy if a man asks if he can kiss you? if you answered yes to both questions, you're being hypocritical, and a part of the problem. i hesitate to use such strong language, but it's simply true. men are under two very strong and very contradictory pressures in society today: on one hand, to be good feminists who care about #metoo, and on the other hand, to hold up the stereotypical manly role of initiating physical contact without "ruining the moment." this is a literally impossible position to be in. can you imagine the confusion and pressure? ⠀
the thing about gender relations and norms is that women can be part of the problem, too. we can reinforce harmful behaviors and stereotypes, too. if we want to reform gender relations for the better, then it's our obligation not just to analyze, critique, and reform others, but also ourselves. contrary to what many women tell me, it is not impossible to change what you're into. it really isn't. it just takes introspection. it takes deconstructing your biases. it takes looking at things you had previously ignored because society told you to (e.g., gentle men, communicative men) in a new, appreciative light. and maybe you don't want to change what you're into, but that requires honesty with yourself and others and communication, too. in today's world it is only fair that we make it clear what we want from and with the men in our life. so shall we do some digging and get to work? 🔧🔧🔧 #consentculture #metoo #feminism #genderrelations #whatwomenwant #unpopularopinion"

text: i am asian, indonesian and chinese. i am bisexual. i am a survivor. and i am a woman. there are many identities behind this face. you and i do not have a singular narrative. she and he and they do not have a single identity. do not categorize people with unheard stories based off the single story you have heard. we consist of many faces, each with endless stories. do not judge, assume, or categorize those ideas and stories foreign to you. time after and time again, women — people — lift others to only put them down. do not claim to promote diversity and adversity if you can not identify one from another. open your mind and heart to listen rather than hear the voices you claim to support. thank you. #intersectionalfeminism #metoo #identity

text:
r. kelly’s still itching to get in his studio. 
right after lifetime premiered its six-part surviving r. kelly documentray, the singer’s chicago studio was flooded with officers after kelly’s victims spoke of the venue that he used as a residence as well. we previously posted about the evidence cops found that proved that the disgraced singer was, in fact, living there with his ‘sex slaves’ which led to him having restricted access.

new reports from tmz detail how the “ignition” singer has requested to have more access to his studio space specifically for late hours between 8 pm and 7 am. apparently, that’s when r. kelly puts in the best work for his music. documents drafted up by the singer say these are also the working hours for his employees. 
when cops did a follow-up inspection of the studio a bed was still present which kelly says he uses after spending 15 hours in the studio and needs a place to crash. a bunch of other personal items are still in the studio such as a massage table, shower and clothes. 
more recently, r. kelly canceled his “king of r&b” tour that would have taken him to to australia, sri lanka, and new zealand. we’re not too sure why he thought it would a good time to go on tour, but someone clearly passed along the message pulling all the promotion off social media.  get the full details at www.itskenbarbie.com do you think kelly should be granted the access? #rkelly #robertkelly #survivingrkelly #lifetime #lifetimetv #muterkelly #metoo #philly #entertainment #entertainmentnews #entertainmentblog #gossip

text:
a young lady surfer has been left speechless today after a group of men allowed her catch a set wave while surfing her local break.the female, who is usually only allowed to have the scraps on the inside that none of the men want, was in awe as she paddled into the wave without being hassled or dropped in on by a man.“yeah i consider myself a bit of a feminist” said one of the local males who gave her permission to catch the wave, “i love chicks. why shouldn’t we let her have a wave. in this day and age with all the #metoo’s and that, chicks should be allowed to vote and stuff. plus the wsl is paying them the same as the fellas so if its good enough for mr ziff then its good enough for me.”the female received plenty of positive reviews of her ride on the way back out with one spectator saying “she surfs pretty good for a chick” and another 60 year old longboarder giving her tips on how to improve her bottom turn.the luck of the young gurfer changed soon after as a “local” who has been surfing for 25 years and still can't do a re-entry, paddled out and proceeded to burn her multiple times, sending her back to the inside for the rest of the session.
📷 @surfmombrit .

text:
i know i’ve said this before, but it’s so important - men are vulnerable. we’re taught that we’re not supposed to be, but we are. we’re vulnerable to heartache, mental illness, trauma, and so on. but male vulnerability is often equated with weakness, which in turn is associated with shame. so why would a man decidedly make himself vulnerable to get the help he needs? how does a man know when vulnerability is no longer a weakness but a strength? that shame associated with being vulnerable plays a big role in why suicide is the leading cause of death in men under 50. it’s time we break through the barriers of shame for ourselves and for the next generation who watches us so closely. seek the help you need; you can start with a visit to your general practitioner, contacting your insurance company to see what mental health services are covered by your plan, or getting online to research what low-cost clinics are in your nearby area. there are also countless hotlines waiting to help, all of which can be found with a quick google search (many are regional and can direct you to local resources). get plugged in! and if you suspect a man in your life is struggling with mental health issues, approach him and share your concern. it could save his life!

on april 16, 2017, in the village of shambhupura in banswara, rajasthan, india, kachru, 21, and monica, 19, got married and were cousins but there family, was not fine with it. the couple were paraded naked, beaten, and sexually assaulted by the whole village of shambhupura and family members including their fathers, brothers and, uncles.
-
-
"the men and children of the village have fled to some other place due to the fear of arrest.
according to the police, on thursday, varaseng resident varanseng resident lord ratna maida, twenty-four-year-old padla resident shankar son lalji, kundelia resident forgotten wife dhulia, resident of shambhupura, gutu son shyama, subhash son hiraji, kangi son kalu, dilip son chetan, ramatu wife kalu and bhusli wife bheema was arrested earlier, nine people including the father of the girl were arrested on wednesday."

text:
here. in this season  of unknowns, uncertainties and the ups and the downs. i have to intentionally choose to trust god daily. with my present and future, and with the outcomes. some days it feels impossible to trust and let go. luckily our feels dont dictate reality.

still a queen 👑✊.
.
.
.

text:
update on the lady who was assaulted by a group of men in edo state, nigeria. 
god bless nigeria for following up with this case of jungle justice. thanks to everyone who fought for this poor lady. 🙏🏽
.
•
•
official police statement 
in reply please quote 
ref no. cz.5300/fprd/fhq/abj/vol.2/5 
date: 7th february, 2019 
the director of news ……………………………. ​press release

re: viral video of indecent assault on a young nigerian lady * npf records breakthrough * arrest six (6) male suspects * pledges justice for the victim

operatives of the nigeria police force have arrested six male suspects involved in the shocking, barbaric and indecent assault meted out on a young nigerian female as shown in a video which recently went viral.

following the dehumanizing incident, the inspector general of police, igp mohammed adamu had ordered a comprehensive investigation into the report.

consequently, the edo state police command, led by its commissioner of police, cp hakeem odumosu swung into action, leading to the investigative breakthrough.

two other male suspects are still at large. efforts are being intensified to arrest them and bring all involved to justice.

the nigeria police force condemns jungle justice in its entirety and warns of dire consequences for persons who resort to criminal acts of self-help.

text:
on january 9th, 2019, the new york senate introduces a bill titled the “reproductive health act”. it is important to note that, prior to this act, abortions were very restricted after 24 weeks, or the second trimester of pregnancy. this act was not an entirely new bill, but it was instead an amendment to the old new york abortion laws. the changes made include: the legalization of abortion “at any time when necessary to protect a women’s life or health”, the allowance of medical professionals who are not doctors to perform abortions, and the repealing of criminal charges for harming unborn children. (source for this part of the info: https://www.nysenate.gov/legislation/bills/2019/s240)
______________________________________________________
supporters of the bill said that it was necessary for these changes to be made to protect the reproductive right of women who want to have abortions in case roe v. wade was overturned (source: https://buffalonews.com/2019/01/22/long-stalled-abortion-bill-passes-new-york-legislature/). supporters also claim that the bill was needed to take abortion out of the state criminal codes and make it public health law instead (source: https://wqad.com/2019/01/25/how-new-yorks-abortion-law-has-changed/) deniers of this bill claimed that the wording of the bill, specifically the part that allows for abortion “at any time when necessary to protect a women’s life or health” claim that this vague wording allows for abortions to happen up until moments before the baby is born (source: https://buffalonews.com/2019/01/22/long-stalled-abortion-bill-passes-new-york-legislature/). another complaint of deniers of the bill was that, if a fetus was killed because of an assault on a women, that person could now not be prosecuted due to the repeal of criminal charges for harming unborn fetuses (source: https://www-m.cnn.com/2019/01/23/health/new-york-abortion-measures-trnd/index.html?r=https%3a%2f%)
_____________________________________________________
after seeing this info, what are your opinions on the new new york abortion laws? feel free to tell us below ⤵️

text:
rp @worldanimalnews_ for over 35 years, #wisconsin residents have celebrated “ridgeland pioneer days” featuring the “free chicken fly” as its main attraction. this activity involves throwing over 200 terrified #chickens from rooftops into a boisterous crowd waiting below.😡🐓
-
the “free chicken fly” event will likely be held on february 16, 2019. it is probable that the date has not been announced in order to stop the efforts of animal advocates.
-
please politely urge #dunncounty officials to end this barbaric event! contact dunn county sheriff kevin bygd 📞(715) 232-1564 or email kbygd@co.dunn.wi.us
-
you can also send @ida_international’s letter to dunn county’s officials by filling out the form🖋👆 (link in our bio)
-

text:
are things at home feeling a bit disorderly?

i urge families to find the routine that models the behaviors you want to see. it’s tough at first but it will work if you’re true to your family’s lifestyle. everybody’s family is different. seeing my girls just fall in line this morning is a win for many reasons, but if any it’s a testament of perseverance and patience. 💖 🙏🏾🙌🏾 when we first started homeschooling i was very disorganized. mostly because i didn’t know what i was supposed to be organizing. my daughter had a love for learning early on in her development she was so curious and eager to explore the world around her. 
it was a constant challenge to keep her stimulated with toys and activities she enjoyed. it wasn’t until we decided to homeschool and tailoring her teachings to her interest thy we saw improvement. the energy around schools ignores everything’s else we do in our day and we take our daily routine seriously we’ve saw progress in emotional stability and concentration on i trusted tasks especially with my toddler. 
modeling the behavior day in and day our girls have positive habits to lead and to mimic. as a result my stress and anxiety has gone done significantly, trying to juggle my attention between my girls, my self and their dad has taken its tile at time, but we are loving this rhythm. everyone has a role and we work together as a team. 
#keepworkingonit

text:
the accusation against justin fairfax resurfaced over the weekend after democratic gov. ralph northam faced calls for resignation following the discovery of a racist photo on his medical school yearbook page. 
vanessa tyson, a professor at scripps college, publicly identified herself as fairfax's accuser on wednesday and released a lengthy statement detailing her version of events.

tyson said fairfax forced her to perform nonconsensual oral sex at the 2004 democratic national convention.

sen. kamala harris of california told reporters thursday that tyson's statement "reads as a credible account" and called for an investigation into the incident.

sen. cory booker of new jersey, another 2020 candidate, told cnn the allegation was "deeply, deeply disturbing" and praised tyson for coming forward. he, too called for an investigation.

sen. kirsten gillibrand of new york praised tyson's courage wednesday night on podcast "lovett or leave it," saying that her account is credible and disturbing and warrants investigation.
.
.
.

text: book 7: beartown by fredrick backman. this book absolutely blew me away. it’s a story about a small hockey town in the middle of a forest fighting for survival. they rely on their team to win- because if they do, they’ll bring in sponsors and schools and commerce. but treating these kids like gods carrying the weight of their town’s livelihood on their shoulders comes at a price. it all blows up, the lines between right & wrong are blurred, and this book, which is about a hockey town, becomes way more than that. it’s about friendship and pride and the things parents will do for their kids and about believing victims and holding your values tight. beartown is beautifully written, the prose so gorgeous that it took me twice as long to read because i kept stopping to soak it in. this book couldn’t be more relevant than right now, as we wade through the thick of the #metoo movement. this is a book that should be taught in high school. i highly recommend reading, even if hockey isn’t your thing- because i promise, it’s about so much more than that.

text:
- this was steve bannon's baby, said former contractor christopher wylie, who described cambridge analytica as "bannon's arsenal of weaponry to wage a culture war on america using military strategies."
.
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
wylie, who worked for scl, the british-based parent of cambridge analytica, told the senate judiciary committee that cambridge analytica hired hackers to collect data it then used against opponents of its political clients.

allegations of the improper use of data for 87 million facebook users by cambridge analytica, which was hired by trump's 2016 election campaign, have led to investigations in the united states and europe.

bannon worked on trump's campaign and became a white house aide when trump took office in january 2017. bannon left in august 2017.

wylie, who has provided reports about how the firm used data facebook collected, on wednesday described discussions at the company about suppressing the vote, exploiting racial tensions, and testing campaign slogans in 2014 for use in the 2016 election.
.
- one of the things that did provoke me to leave was the beginnings of discussions of voter disengagement, i have seen documents reference and i recall conversations that it was intended to focus on african-american voters, wylie said. - the company learned that there were segments of the population that responded to messages like 'drain the swamp' or images of border walls or indeed paranoia about the 'deep state' that weren't necessarily reflected in mainstream polling or mainstream political discourse that steve bannon was interested in to help build his movement, wylie said.

another witness who testified to the judiciary committee, tufts university associate professor eitan hersh, said he was "skeptical" of the effectiveness that such political messaging and targeting. - no person is persuadable all the time, he said.

mark hosenball
reuters

text:
i've watched the qspiracy since day one.

steve bannon left the wh august 2017 and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences? 'j-c' church militant, anyone?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit a hijacked party is just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt, with the goonsquad known as gop, has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this and messes with the boombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on me me me bed. obviously someone has a lot to lose when none of the us intelligence agencies ends this loonatic travesty.

qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that goebbels would have died for. it is clear that stuff like pizzagate™ was testing and groundwork for the 2016 election and since it proved to be very effective it is used still.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are useless with the content - no way they are going to risk their business by taking responsibility.

there is no way that gop isn't aware of this - after all, cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole narrative is built on the same facebook user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got as cambridge analytica. pedofiles - i bet - but the way things are bundled sure makes goebbels shiver.

trump plays along with his tweets, gestures and words. the bigger issue still - the republicans willingly piggybacked this before the midterms and still keep abusing the faith of their fellow men.

this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

text:
[책씨 22호] 나는 그만두기로 했다
행간을 읽는 사람들(김소영, 나혜, 이재영, 조아라, 김달래, 송미란, 임청명, 유지은, 최예지, 김재이, 이옥수, 이여름) 지음, 900km 펴냄.

2016년 10월, #문단_내_성폭력 운동을 기억한다. 언론에서는 서지현 검사의 성폭력 피해사실 공론화가 #metoo 운동의 시작이라고 하지만, 그 보다 전에 문단 내 성폭력 운동이 있었다. 그로부터 #oo계_내_성폭력 운동은 특히 폐쇄적이고 위계적인 문화예술계를 중심으로 들불처럼 퍼져나갔다. 이 전에는 가해지목인의 혐의 사실이 확정되기 전까지 ‘가해자 oo’으로 공론화를 하던 움직임이, 문단 내 성폭력 운동부터는 거침없이 가해자의 이름을 공개하고, 명예훼손으로 고소를 당하면 후원금을 모아 피해자를 지지하며 당차게 앞으로 나아갔다. 이제는 당하지만은 않겠다는 의지. 피해자로만 머물지 않겠다는 도약.

900km가 펴낸 <나는 그만두기로 했다>는 누구에게도 말 못할 피해사실을 간직하고 있던 이들을 세상 밖으로 나서게 했던 #문단_내_성폭력 운동의 결실(?)이라 말할 수 있을까. 이 책은 2018년 봄, d대학교 문예창작과 내에서 있었던 미투운동에서 시작되었다. 교내에서 발생한 교수의 성폭력 사건의 진상을 규명하고 건강한 발전 방안을 마련하기 위해 졸업생과 재학생들이 자발적으로 연대하고 싸운 결과 가해자 교수는 강단에서 물러났고, 학교 내 반성폭력 규정과 문화를 형성하는 성과를 이룬다.

그 ‘이후’ 젠더 감수성이 결여되고, 등단을 통해서만 글을 발표할 수 있는 폐쇄적 구조에 대한 문제의식으로 ‘행간을 읽는 사람들(김소영, 나혜, 이재영, 조아라, 김달래, 송미란, 임청명, 유지은, 최예지, 김재이, 이옥수, 이여름)’은 글을 썼다. “위계와 폭력으로부터 피해자를 위로하고 우리를 지키기 위해.” 이 책은 10편의 시와 8편의 소설이 ‘그만둠’을 선언한다. ‘엄마’는 ‘엄마를 그만 두기’로 하고, ‘나’는 공소시효가 끝난 성폭력 피해에 대해 대응을 ‘그만 두기’로 하며, 아들만 귀하게 여기는 집에서 자란 ‘선희’는 오빠를 위한 선의의 거짓말을 ‘그만 두기’로 한다. 
에필로그에서 이옥수는 이렇게 말한다. “한국에는 소위 ‘문단’이 있습니다. 이 문단은 신춘문예 당선, 문예지 신인상, 신인 추천 등을 통해 소위 ‘등단’이라는 것을 해야 진입할 수 있습니다. 오늘날의 ‘문단’은 더는 그 기능을 하지 못하고 있습니다. 슬프게도 가해자의 대부분은 등단한 작가이고, 피해자는 등단을 원하는 작가 지망생이었습니다. 
우리는 분노합니다. 문단이 가지고 있는 구조적인 문제, 예술이라는 미명하에 행해지는 폐단, 젠더 감수성이 결여된 공동체 등 눈에 보이는 폭력에서부터 보이지 않는 은밀한 폭력까지 그것들은 여전히 우리를 위협합니다. 그래서 우리는 그만두기로 했습니다. 위계와 폭력에 관한 무지와 외면을. 그리고 누군가의 취향에 따라 작가가 되거나 작가가 되지 못하는 폐쇄적인 구조를.” 이 책을 입고하자마자 가장 먼저 떠오른 사람은 한 살 터울의 언니였다. 학창시절 시 쓰기를 좋아했던 언니는 직장을 다니다가 뒤늦게 문예창작과에 입학했다. 졸업 작품으로 (나는 잘 모르는) 어떤 문예지에 등단한 언니는 인쇄된 책을 들고 한껏 웃으며 가족들에게 자랑을 했더랬다. 하지만 졸업식을 앞두고 인사를 드리러 찾아간 교수님을 뵙고 온 언니는 시 쓰기를 ‘그만 두었다’. 교수의 말이 ‘내가 너를 등단 시켜 주었으니 사례를 해야 하는 것 아니냐’며 은근 슬쩍 금전을 요구했다는 것이다. 본인의 실력으로 등단을 한 줄 알았던 언니는 실망을 금치 못하고 그 날로 시와는 연을 끊은 듯 했다. <나는 그만두기로 했다>를 언니에게 선물하고 싶었다. 그리고 다시 시를 쓰는 언니를 보고 싶었다. “언니, 시집 하나 사줄까?” 돌아오는 대답은 간단했다. “시 안 읽은 지 10년이 넘었다”

무엇이 그토록 시를 좋아하는 그녀를 ‘그만 두’게 만들었을까. 언니의 선택은 “나의 의지에 의해서가 아닌 위계와 폭력에 의해 선택되어지는 모든 것들로부터 ‘그만둠’을 선언”하는 것이었을까. -지하 씀

[책씨 22호] 나는 그만두기로 했다
행간을 읽는 사람들(김소영, 나혜, 이재영, 조아라, 김달래, 송미란, 임청명, 유지은, 최예지, 김재이, 이옥수, 이여름) 지음, 900km 펴냄.

2016년 10월,  운동을 기억한다. 언론에서는 서지현 검사의 성폭력 피해사실 공론화가  운동의 시작이라고 하지만, 그 보다 전에 문단 내 성폭력 운동이 있었다. 그로부터  운동은 특히 폐쇄적이고 위계적인 문화예술계를 중심으로 들불처럼 퍼져나갔다. 이 전에는 가해지목인의 혐의 사실이 확정되기 전까지 ‘가해자 oo’으로 공론화를 하던 움직임이, 문단 내 성폭력 운동부터는 거침없이 가해자의 이름을 공개하고, 명예훼손으로 고소를 당하면 후원금을 모아 피해자를 지지하며 당차게 앞으로 나아갔다. 이제는 당하지만은 않겠다는 의지. 피해자로만 머물지 않겠다는 도약.

900km가 펴낸 <나는 그만두기로 했다>는 누구에게도 말 못할 피해사실을 간직하고 있던 이들을 세상 밖으로 나서게 했던  운동의 결실(?)이라 말할 수 있을까. 이 책은 2018년 봄, d대학교 문예창작과 내에서 있었던 미투운동에서 시작되었다. 교내에서 발생한 교수의 성폭력 사건의 진상을 규명하고 건강한 발전 방안을 마련하기 위해 졸업생과 재학생들이 자발적으로 연대하고 싸운 결과 가해자 교수는 강단에서 물러났고, 학교 내 반성폭력 규정과 문화를 형성하는 성과를 이룬다.

그 ‘이후’ 젠더 감수성이 결여되고, 등단을 통해서만 글을 발표할 수 있는 폐쇄적 구조에 대한 문제의식으로 ‘행간을 읽는 사람들(김소영, 나혜, 이재영, 조아라, 김달래, 송미란, 임청명, 유지은, 최예지, 김재이, 이옥수, 이여름)’은 글을 썼다. “위계와 폭력으로부터 피해자를 위로하고 우리를 지키기 위해.” 이 책은 10편의 시와 8편의 소설이 ‘그만둠’을 선언한다. ‘엄마’는 ‘엄마를 그만 두기’로 하고, ‘나’는 공소시효가 끝난 성폭력 피해에 대해 대응을 ‘그만 두기’로 하며, 아들만 귀하게 여기는 집에서 자란 ‘선희’는 오빠를 위한 선의의 거짓말을 ‘그만 두기’로 한다. 
에필로그에서 이옥수는 이렇게 말한다. “한국에는 소위 ‘문단’이 있습니다. 이 문단은 신춘문예 당선, 문예지 신인상, 신인 추천 등을 통해 소위 ‘등단’이라는 것을 해야 진입할 수 있습니다. 오늘날의 ‘문단’은 더는 그 기능을 하지 못하고 있습니다. 슬프게도 가해자의 대부분은 등단한 작가이고, 피해자는 등단을 원하는 작가 지망생이었습니다. 
우리는 분노합니다. 문단이 가지고 있는 구조적인 문제, 예술이라는 미명하에 행해지는 폐단, 젠더 감수성이 결여된 공동체 등 눈에 보이는 폭력에서부터 보이지 않는 은밀한 폭력까지 그것들은 여전히 우리를 위협합니다. 그래서 우리는 그만두기로 했습니다. 위계와 폭력에 관한 무지와 외면을. 그리고 누군가의 취향에 따라 작가가 되거나 작가가 되지 못하는 폐쇄적인 구조를.” 이 책을 입고하자마자 가장 먼저 떠오른 사람은 한 살 터울의 언니였다. 학창시절 시 쓰기를 좋아했던 언니는 직장을 다니다가 뒤늦게 문예창작과에 입학했다. 졸업 작품으로 (나는 잘 모르는) 어떤 문예지에 등단한 언니는 인쇄된 책을 들고 한껏 웃으며 가족들에게 자랑을 했더랬다. 하지만 졸업식을 앞두고 인사를 드리러 찾아간 교수님을 뵙고 온 언니는 시 쓰기를 ‘그만 두었다’. 교수의 말이 ‘내가 너를 등단 시켜 주었으니 사례를 해야 하는 것 아니냐’며 은근 슬쩍 금전을 요구했다는 것이다. 본인의 실력으로 등단을 한 줄 알았던 언니는 실망을 금치 못하고 그 날로 시와는 연을 끊은 듯 했다. <나는 그만두기로 했다>를 언니에게 선물하고 싶었다. 그리고 다시 시를 쓰는 언니를 보고 싶었다. “언니, 시집 하나 사줄까?” 돌아오는 대답은 간단했다. “시 안 읽은 지 10년이 넘었다”

무엇이 그토록 시를 좋아하는 그녀를 ‘그만 두’게 만들었을까. 언니의 선택은 “나의 의지에 의해서가 아닌 위계와 폭력에 의해 선택되어지는 모든 것들로부터 ‘그만둠’을 선언”하는 것이었을까. -지하 씀

) 이라 말할 수 있을까 . 이 책은 2018년 봄 , d대학교 문예창작과 내에서 있었던 미투운동에서 시작되었다 . 교내에서 발생한 교수의 성폭력 사건의 진상을 규명하고 건강한 발전 방안을 마련하기 위해 졸업생과 재학생들이 자발적으로 연대하고 싸운 결과 가해자 교수는 강단에서 물러났고 , 학교 내 반성폭력 규정과 문화를 형성하는 성과를 이룬다 . 그 ‘ 이후 ’ 젠더 감수성이 결여되고 , 등단을 통해서만 글을 발표할 수 있는 폐쇄적 구조에 대한 문제의식으로 ‘ 행간을 읽는 사람들 ( 김소영 , 나혜 , 이재영 , 조아라 , 김달래 , 송미란 , 임청명 , 유지은 , 최예지 , 김재이 , 이옥수 , 이여름 ) ’ 은 글을 썼다 . “ 위계와 폭력으로부터 피해자를 위로하고 우리를 지키기 위해 . ” 이 책은 10편의 시와 8편의 소설이 ‘ 그만둠 ’ 을 선언한다 . ‘ 엄마 ’ 는 ‘ 엄마를 그만 두기 ’ 로 하고 , ‘ 나 ’ 는 공소시효가 끝난 성폭력 피해에 대해 대응을 ‘ 그만 두기 ’ 로 하며 , 아들만 귀하게 여기는 집에서 자란 ‘ 선희 ’ 는 오빠를 위한 선의의 거짓말을 ‘ 그만 두기 ’ 로 한다 . 에필로그에서 이옥수는 이렇게 말한다 . “ 한국에는 소위 ‘ 문단 ’ 이 있습니다 . 이 문단은 신춘문예 당선 , 문예지 신인상 , 신인 추천 등을 통해 소위 ‘ 등단 ’ 이라는 것을 해야 진입할 수 있습니다 . 오늘날의 ‘ 문단 ’ 은 더는 그 기능을 하지 못하고 있습니다 . 슬프게도 가해자의 대부분은 등단한 작가이고 , 피해자는 등단을 원하는 작가 지망생이었습니다 . 우리는 분노합니다 . 문단이 가지고 있는 구조적인 문제 , 예술이라는 미명하에 행해지는 폐단 , 젠더 감수성이 결여된 공동체 등 눈에 보이는 폭력에서부터 보이지 않는 은밀한 폭력까지 그것들은 여전히 우리를 위협합니다 . 그래서 우리는 그만두기로 했습니다 . 위계와 폭력에 관한 무지와 외면을 . 그리고 누군가의 취향에 따라 작가가 되거나 작가가 되지 못하는 폐쇄적인 구조를 . ” 이 책을 입고하자마자 가장 먼저 떠오른 사람은 한 살 터울의 언니였다 . 학창시절 시 쓰기를 좋아했던 언니는 직장을 다니다가 뒤늦게 문예창작과에 입학했다 . 졸업 작품으로 ( 나는 잘 모르는 ) 어떤 문예지에 등단한 언니는 인쇄된 책을 들고 한껏 웃으며 가족들에게 자랑을 했더랬다 . 하지만 졸업식을 앞두고 인사를 드리러 찾아간 교수님을 뵙고 온 언니는 시 쓰기를 ‘ 그만 두었다 ’ . 교수의 말이 ‘ 내가 너를 등단 시켜 주었으니 사례를 해야 하는 것 아니냐 ’ 며 은근 슬쩍 금전을 요구했다는 것이다 . 본인의 실력으로 등단을 한 줄 알았던 언니는 실망을 금치 못하고 그 날로 시와는 연을 끊은 듯 했다 . < 나는 그만두기로 했다 > 를 언니에게 선물하고 싶었다 . 그리고 다시 시를 쓰는 언니를 보고 싶었다 . “ 언니 , 시집 하나 사줄까 ? text:
📆 one month to go to international women’s day!

it’s one of our favourite days of the year as we stop to acknowledge and celebrate all the advances made by diverse women for equal rights around the world.

it’s also an important time for us to come together for support, and to recommit ourselves to the work ahead.

keep an eye out for ways to get involved over the next few weeks.

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
but wylie wasn’t just talking about fashion. he had recently been exposed to a new discipline: “information operations”, which ranks alongside land, sea, air and space in the us military’s doctrine of the “five-dimensional battle space”. his brief ranged across the scl group – the british government has paid scl to conduct counter-extremism operations in the middle east, and the us department of defense has contracted it to work in afghanistan.

i tell him that another former employee described the firm as “mi6 for hire”, and i’d never quite understood it.
.
- it’s like dirty mi6 because you’re not constrained. there’s no having to go to a judge to apply for permission. it’s normal for a ‘market research company’ to amass data on domestic populations. and if you’re working in some country and there’s an auxiliary benefit to a current client with aligned interests, well that’s just a bonus.
.
when i ask how bannon even found scl, wylie tells me what sounds like a tall tale, though it’s one he can back up with an email about how mark block, a veteran republican strategist, happened to sit next to a cyberwarfare expert for the us air force on a plane. - and the cyberwarfare guy is like, ‘oh, you should meet scl. they do cyberwarfare for elections.’
.
it was bannon who took this idea to the mercers: robert mercer – the co-ceo of the hedge fund renaissance technologies, who used his billions to pursue a rightwing agenda, donating to republican causes and supporting republican candidates – and his daughter rebekah.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
- this was steve bannon's baby, said former contractor christopher wylie, who described cambridge analytica as "bannon's arsenal of weaponry to wage a culture war on america using military strategies."
.
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

text:
today i was notified that justice was served!!! my sweet friend was strong, powerful, talented, beautiful and fierce, she was a mommy and an entrepreneur and she deserved the world but her world was cut short by a weak ass, jealous man. today the man that was supposed to love her will remain locked behind bars where he belongs. justice!!!! i want to leave you all with this. your partner should empower you, not de-power you!!! he/she should add strength to who you are, be a source of healthy energy. if it’s taking life from you and only draining you, get rid of it!!! no matter what it is!!!! your man, your woman, your friend, your business, i don’t give a shit what, if it’s not serving you well let it go, in fact open the door and kick its ass out. life is way to short & fragile to ever give your life power to another. if you don't know how you can leave those unhealthy relationships, please message me whether we know each other in real life or not i'm here! this isn't the only tragedy of domestic violence i've personally come across in my life and even typing these words i feel nauseous. trust me, there's help you just need to do the first step and tell someone you're in a bad situation. i love you amber kay, your story will never die!!!! till we see each other again 💋

text:
#투데이뮤직 #metoo #meghantrainor 
#ifeelpretty @genie_music 
영화 ost로 유명한데. 
제작사 요청으로 영화쪽으로는 재생이 안되고. 
가수의 앨범에서 재생해서 들음. 노래가 경쾌하다. 
영화도 아주 재미있게 봤다. 
영화가 성공하는 요소는 여럿있겠지만
근래에 접한 영화를 들어서 생각해보면 
일단 알고 있는 소재를 어떤게 변주하는가에 따라 
관객의 반응을 쉽게 얻을수 있다는걸 이해했다. 
각색이라는 분야로 생각하면
이미 나온 이야기들을 
새롭게 만드는 이야기로 신선함을 주느냐가 관건인듯

text:
wylie, who worked for scl, the british-based parent of cambridge analytica, told the senate judiciary committee that cambridge analytica hired hackers to collect data it then used against opponents of its political clients.

allegations of the improper use of data for 87 million facebook users by cambridge analytica, which was hired by trump's 2016 election campaign, have led to investigations in the united states and europe.

bannon worked on trump's campaign and became a white house aide when trump took office in january 2017. bannon left in august 2017.

wylie, who has provided reports about how the firm used data facebook collected, on wednesday described discussions at the company about suppressing the vote, exploiting racial tensions, and testing campaign slogans in 2014 for use in the 2016 election.
.
- one of the things that did provoke me to leave was the beginnings of discussions of voter disengagement, i have seen documents reference and i recall conversations that it was intended to focus on african-american voters, wylie said. - the company learned that there were segments of the population that responded to messages like 'drain the swamp' or images of border walls or indeed paranoia about the 'deep state' that weren't necessarily reflected in mainstream polling or mainstream political discourse that steve bannon was interested in to help build his movement, wylie said.

another witness who testified to the judiciary committee, tufts university associate professor eitan hersh, said he was "skeptical" of the effectiveness that such political messaging and targeting. - no person is persuadable all the time, he said.

mark hosenball
reuters

ca now celebrates black history &  power leaders: 
we are seizing the opportunity to honor the too-often neglected accomplishments of black americans in every area of endeavor.  the month of february is set aside to serve as a  powerful reminder that we stand on the shoulders of greatness. we are reminded this is not a race but a relay. we remain committed to intersectional gender equity, honoring our past and developing new leaders. join us in celebrating our political, cultural, and social transformational leadership.

on this day, we honor tarana burke! share this post to celebrate this civil rights activist and her incredible contributions to black culture/politics, as well as the #metoo movement. #powerleaders #nowtrendsetters.

text:
today is a day to ‘shine a light on human trafficking’.
.
my hands have hugged women and children who’ve survived human trafficking and sexual exploitation in america and overseas. my hands have told johns who were trying to purchase me no. my hands have shaken as i testified at the massachusetts state house against trafficking. my hands have called emergency hotline numbers with a woman while on a beach vacation. my hands have played board games with children rescued from a cybersex ring in the philippines. and my hands have prayed for so many still in hiding.
.
this is an issue near to my heart. there are over 40 million being trafficked today and many in our own backyards. today your hands could bring awareness to one of the biggest issues of our time. just draw a red x and take the opportunities to tell people about modern day slavery and the #enditmovement. #inittoendit❌
.
“speak up for those who cannot speak for themselves; ensure justice for those being crushed. yes, speak up for the poor and helpless, and see that they get justice.” proverbs 31: 8-9

text:
- what we worked on was ... data harvesting programs where we would pull data from users of apps and all of their friend networks and run that data through algorithms that could profile their personality traits and other psychological attributes, wylie told cnn’s don lemon monday evening.

wylie said the ultimate goal was to obtain information in order to exploit mental vulnerabilities that our algorithms showed that [facebook users] had.

in addition to wylie and cambridge analytica, accounts of cambridge analytica’s parent company, strategic communication laboratories, and those of a university of cambridge psychologist aleksandr kogan were also suspended.

the accounts were suspended because facebook received reports that data that had been shared with cambridge and wylie from kogan’s app may not have been completely deleted. kogan’s app was removed in 2015 and facebook said they had been previously provided certifications that the data had been deleted. - several days ago, we received reports that, contrary to the certifications we were given, not all data was deleted, facebook said friday. - we are moving aggressively to determine the accuracy of these claims. if true, this is another unacceptable violation of trust and the commitments they made. we are suspending scl/cambridge analytica, wylie and kogan from facebook, pending further information.

special counsel robert mueller asked cambridge analytica last fall to surrender emails from any of its employees who worked for the trump campaign, the wall street journal reported in december. the firm complied to the request.

diana stancy correll
washington examiner

the accounts were suspended because facebook received reports that data that had been shared with cambridge and wylie from kogan’s app may not have been completely deleted. kogan’s app was removed in 2015 and facebook said they had been previously provided certifications that the data had been deleted. - several days ago, we received reports that, contrary to the certifications we were given, not all data was deleted, facebook said friday. - we are moving aggressively to determine the accuracy of these claims. if true, this is another unacceptable violation of trust and the commitments they made. we are suspending scl/cambridge analytica, wylie and kogan from facebook, pending further information.

special counsel robert mueller asked cambridge analytica last fall to surrender emails from any of its employees who worked for the trump campaign, the wall street journal reported in december. the firm complied to the request.

diana stancy correll
washington examiner

text:
________________________________________человек спросил у жизни: - почему я так живу? жизнь для меня сплошное разочарование... и жизнь ответила ему: - потому что ты живешь напоказ. а где же ты настоящий? нужно быть, а не казаться. вот тогда ты и будешь счастлив.******************************как важно в жизни быть,
а не казаться.
как важно в ней любить –
не притворяться.
как важно говорить
и не стесняться.
в проступках не бояться
признаваться. 
как важно сделать вид –
не возмущаться.
от дуновений быта –
не сломаться.
назло невзгодам – нагло
улыбаться.
и от презрений важно
удержаться. 
как важно день прожить
без провокаций,
без гнусных надоевших
махинаций.
по морю жизни – плыть,
но не скитаться,
и у причалов нужных
швартоваться. 
как сложно одолеть
все эти «важно»,
чтоб духом не болеть -
быть отважным.
как сложно в жизни быть,
а не казаться,
при этом - человеком
оставаться. стихи.ру

text:
u.s. president donald trump's former aide steve bannon sought to use personal information collected online to promote "a culture war," a whistleblower on now-defunct political data firm cambridge analytica told u.s. senators on wednesday.

bannon, a former cambridge analytica vice president, "saw cultural warfare as a means to create enduring change in american politics," testified christopher wylie, who says information about tens of millions of facebook users ended up in cambridge analytica's hands.

bannon's attorney william burck did not immediately respond to an email request for comment on wylie's testimony.

wylie, who worked for scl, the british-based parent of cambridge analytica, told the senate judiciary committee that cambridge analytica hired hackers to collect data it then used against opponents of its political clients.

allegations of the improper use of data for 87 million facebook users by cambridge analytica, which was hired by trump's 2016 election campaign, have led to investigations in the united states and europe.

mark hosenball
reuters

text:
💚 importante:
una de cada 20 niñas y mujeres han sufrido alguna forma de mutilación genital femenina (mgf), según cifras de naciones unidas (onu).
eso significa que 200 millones de mujeres en la actualidad han sido sometidas a algún tipo de corte, cambio o eliminación de la parte externa de sus genitales.
y la onu ha hecho un llamado para acabar con esta práctica, también conocida como ablación genital, en el día de la tolerancia cero de la mgf, que se celebra cada 6 de febrero.
·
·

·
·

text_retweet:
#repost @flyingjoyfulbird
• • • • •
小項目 1：[noabuse_flyingjoyfulbird] ！❤💧 啟動！

寫在一切之先, 我要先感謝! ❤我要先感謝天父, 因為祢讓我有新生命, 謝謝祢讓我重新有了希望。💝謝謝爸和媽, 這份支持真得來不易呢。 ❤謝謝你們, 我的另一對爸爸媽媽。謝謝天父讓我遇上你們, 謝謝你們的耐心,謝謝你們的愛,謝謝你們提供的配樂,這也是祂賜予的原創音樂。 ❤謝謝娟兒的幫忙, 不是有妳,不會有這小項目,不會有這23秒的小片段。謝謝妳, 天父也給了我這位好朋友。一起畫畫,看戲,談天,被我炮轟(?),一起談論我們的天父,一起痛並愛著我們的家。咬著牙,也要愛下去。

謝謝你們, 也謝謝沒有在(特別鳴謝)出現的你們, 因為你們的愛,有了滋養,也有了生命重整的可能。

我願我愛的香港, 被祝福包圍。
在我生命中出現過, 離開了, 或仍願意停留的你們, 在浮世當中仍有平安, 在黑暗中有希望。

我不想說得離地, 我指的不是什麼大愛,什麼正能量。我真不是什麼正能量人呀。
我不想只講承諾而不承擔。我願我做了一點,看到一點.行一步,見一步。

那是一份萬人阻擋也無法阻攔的決心, 不一定每個人都認同, 也懇請我們都回到當初出於愛的心。

只能躲藏在黑暗裡的, 回到在祂的光中,我們必得見光。

窮困孤寡, 因祂重得盼望。受虐的, 得到幫助和拯救。

人的改變, 原來與環境無關。

我愛的香港人, 我愛的你們, 但願我能為你們做一點小事。

#nomoreabuse #nomoresuicide #love #nomoresexualabuse #nosexualabuse #hope #jesus #godislove #jesus #light #painting #drawing #flyingjoyfulbird #要祝福不要咒詛
#歡迎轉載請註明出處便可 #我們可以失望不要絕望 #truth #nocurse #畫畫 #水彩 #youth #mentalhealth #短片 #youth #girl #wounded #metoo

text:
из вчерашнего прямого эфира про то, почему помогает #visiotuning

считается, что у нас есть более-менее законченная модель окружающего мира, благодаря которой мы можем с этим миром взаимодействовать... так вот - это не так!
.
🎓 «теория тысячи мозгов» (thousand brains theory) про которую я рассказал подробнее на вебинаре, предполагает, что единой цельной модели мира у нас нет. вместо одной есть множество "малых" моделей, которые создаёт каждая часть мозга "под себя". адекватное взаимодействие с реальностью возможно благодаря взаимодействию, "синхронизации" этих частей.

в основе работы нашего сознания, нашего успеха в жизни и нашего здоровья лежит не иерархия мозговых центров или там ценностей, не единая "правильная" модель мира, не "личность", а сложные равноправные сетевые взаимодействия множества частей нашей психики

новая модель работы мозга не только объясняет факты, с которыми не справлялись предыдущие теории, но даёт множество практических решений, которые сделают нас эффективнее, здоровее и счастливее
.
⚠️ только @visiotuning использует современные научные знания, а не заблуждения... хотите наконец получить результаты? начните с бесплатной консультации! пишите заявку в  direct или в мессенджеры!

-

"the men and children of the village have fled to some other place due to the fear of arrest.
according to the police, on thursday, varaseng resident varanseng resident lord ratna maida, twenty-four-year-old padla resident shankar son lalji, kundelia resident forgotten wife dhulia, resident of shambhupura, gutu son shyama, subhash son hiraji, kangi son kalu, dilip son chetan, ramatu wife kalu and bhusli wife bheema was arrested earlier, nine people including the father of the girl were arrested on wednesday."

text:
la comisión feminista de fetec apoya a las denunciantes de óscar arias sánchez. mostramos nuestra unión y acuerpamos su valentía. al día de hoy se contabilizan 7 mujeres que han dado testimonio de comportamientos sexuales inaceptables de parte de oas. nos enfurece que las mujeres enfrentemos violaciones y abusos sexuales en el trabajo, en espacios políticos, en espacios educativos. nos enfurece que se minimice y ridiculice una denuncia tan seria. exigimos justicia y castigo para los machistas. 
brindamos un abrazo sororo a todas las víctimas de acoso y abuso sexual que hayan ocurrido dentro y fuera del tec. estamos para apoyarlxs, escucharlxs, acompañarlxs en el proceso legal y darles la mano en su proceso personal. 
hacemos un llamado a la comunidad de funcionarixs y estudiantes del tec a tomar con seriedad la denuncia formal presentada por la doctora y a no difundir un discurso que perpetue la cultura del silencio.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.

text: this poem resembles some of what us survivors have to overcome. being sexually abused takes a part of you. for most people, it tears them apart. our peace is interrupted. we try to find ways to heal ourselves but struggle greatly doing so. trusting others becomes difficult and can even cause us to build walls. many of us believed that we were the ones to blame. when we try to move forward, at some point we have thought that we are not worthy or even questioned ourselves, “who would even want to be with a person like me?” we have thought that we are not in control because we have all experienced some sort of act of being powerless. before i shared my story, for many years i felt as if i was the only one that had gone through this experience. now that i have opened up to others, many have opened up to me. some were strangers and some were those that i have known very well. if you are a survivor, i am here to listen and learn from your experience. comment below or dm me if you can relate to this poem or if you’re willing to share your story. also follow my other page for more @lifeofanovercomer ❤️ #savethechildren #childabuseawareness #healing #lovewins #growth #lifeofanovercomer #metoo #timesup #mystory #speakup #poems #quotes #mentalhealth #journey #sexualabuse #breakthesilence #livelife #nolongeravictim #support #youarenotalone #truth #strong #trauma #womensrights

text:
http://soundcloud.com/armaan-malde/surviving

the aftermath of childhood abuse is complicated. there's this devastating knowledge that someone has purposefully hobbled you, stolen away developmental milestones that help healthy people relate to one another, build love and trust and friendship. because me finding a real family would have threatened her kingdom.

i got away, but now i'm left to repair the damage. i've grappled with myself day in and day out, is it worth it? a constant struggle between the dream life i've created for myself that i still can't feel present in, and the relief of death. 
i can't really describe the feeling of making that choice so many times. sometimes the things i can't express in words come out in song instead. when they tried to cut me off from everything that could save me, when they tried to choke off my voice, they failed. i may not be able to talk sometimes but i can sing. 
oh yeah link is in my bio if you want something easily clickable ✌️ #survivor #metoo #singersongwriter #munchausenbyproxy #childhoodabuse #ftm

text: my favorite thing about this photo is that my dad made this shirt. (swipe to see him in action!) talking to the people who love us about our sexual trauma can feel impossible or uncomfortable (for both people!) and this was the case for me all my life. part of why i created birdbrain was so that people who have experienced sexual trauma can see that the people who care about us are in solidarity with us even when they can’t find the words. when i decided that birdbrain’s motto would make a nice shirt i immediately asked my dad to write: “we’re not crazy.” not many people would expect a college football coach to be a fashion designer lol but he got the job done. my mom has sewn so many of our samples and now dad finally has his own presence here too. my family and i made this together, and it will be a victory for them too in april when they fly out for our first pop up community showroom. we hope that the challenges we faced and the sacrifices we’ve made to bring people like us comfort will reach as many people who need to hear our message. we’re not crazy! #fashion #style #metoo #metoomovement #styleblogger #fashionblogger #nyc #nycfashion #models @mysterious37

text:
throughout the committee hearing, several republican senators including ted cruz and thom tillis pointed to the obama campaign’s use of facebook data, to highlight the fact that such practices are bipartisan.

however, people who downloaded the obama campaign app were aware they were using a political app. by contrast, the data obtained by cambridge analytica was obtained via a personality quiz application whose users had no idea their data would be used by a political campaign.

cambridge analytica improperly obtained the personal information of millions of facebook users to build profiles of us voters in order to target them with personalised political advertisements, via a related uk-based entity called scl elections.
.
- we exploited facebook to harvest millions of people’s profiles, said wylie in march. - and built models to exploit what we knew about them and target their inner demons. that was the basis the entire company was built on.

wylie has previously told mps at a british select committee that the eu referendum was won through fraud after vote leave allegedly used a network of companies to get round election spending laws. he said he thought there “could have been a different outcome had there not been, in my view, cheating”. he also met privately with house democrats in april, but wednesday’s hearing was his first public appearance before us lawmakers.

olivia solon
the guardian

strangulation....the leading cause of traumatic brain injury #tbi in the us?! it's hard to get back to yourself after this happens to you. trauma changes everything especially feeling safe in your own skin. i've never appreciated or focused on my brian health before this happened now i go to great lengths to protect and heal my brain and it does heal! i mean you are not ever exactly the same but you do heal if you work at it. if this happens to you, you must report it! if you survived you got lucky because it's no different if the weapon was a gun. multiple times will severely injure your brain!

text_retweet:
kita masih agni & tidak akan menyerah

#repost @pikiranlelaki_
• • • • •
ya, kata "damai" itu tidak pernah terucap dari mulut agni, melainkan ia diucapkan secara serampangan oleh mulut kaum patriarki.
.
agni tidak menyerah, agni tidak berdamai. semua dilakukan karena berbagai macam pertimbangan. apapun realitanya, kini kita harus mengelus dada, mendapati negeri ini masih belum mampu menyelesaikan masalah kekerasan seksual dengan baik.
.
kita juga tentu marah, menyadari bahwa kita masih belum dapat bergerak bebas dengan aman dan damai di lingkungan kita sendiri. para pelaku kekerasan seksual tentu masih bebas bergentayangan menghantui kita semua, karena pada akhirnya mereka tidak akan mendapatkan hukuman apapun selain pemakluman.
.
dan korban? kita juga mesti menangis melihat fenomena victim blaming masih menjadi hal yang dianggap harus dilakukan.
.

text:
we got through
and now, we speak.

i.  you, my "old school" date,
told me they equate
scented flowers to
the stinging, yet
silencing smell of chloroform.

ii.  you told me
that this is how "girls" behave,
they submit,
give in,
break,
or else are broken.

iii.  oh, you again, 
the son of that father,
that damned father if i may,
who once told his daughter,
"stay strong, honey. 
always be bold." but then, on the same night,
when he returned,
smelling like alcohol was brewed,
on his collar itself;
who deplored,
and despised, yet
lusted
those tipsy, 
submissive, 
unconscious --oh uh, hey
-- unconscious,
the best type of female.

iv.  they all heard me,
they all heard her,
mind you, but they heard all of them.

and eventhough we got through all of it;
laying awake at nights,
feeling our beds
turn into rocks
is not atypical.

but you know what?
it ends.
and it ends now.

v.  for i see women rising,
and they're stronger this time.

power like they've been 
on their knees for too long.

power like a shade
that towers,
and will continue to,
over upcoming decades of women.

i see women, that have been standing,
their refusal tougher than a mere demand,
of men for women to be victims,
but later survivors.

vi.  allow me to bring something i heard in 
a piece of poetry.
on most days,
i feel more like a victim,
than i am, a survivor.

but i been done giving them what they want.
i been done having my head shook down.
because all we end up being,
is a score for them,
and forgotten for the society.
-nush.v

text:
u.s. president donald trump's former aide steve bannon sought to use personal information collected online to promote "a culture war," a whistleblower on now-defunct political data firm cambridge analytica told u.s. senators on wednesday.

bannon, a former cambridge analytica vice president, "saw cultural warfare as a means to create enduring change in american politics," testified christopher wylie, who says information about tens of millions of facebook users ended up in cambridge analytica's hands.

bannon's attorney william burck did not immediately respond to an email request for comment on wylie's testimony.

wylie, who worked for scl, the british-based parent of cambridge analytica, told the senate judiciary committee that cambridge analytica hired hackers to collect data it then used against opponents of its political clients.

allegations of the improper use of data for 87 million facebook users by cambridge analytica, which was hired by trump's 2016 election campaign, have led to investigations in the united states and europe.

mark hosenball
reuters

text:
throughout the committee hearing, several republican senators including ted cruz and thom tillis pointed to the obama campaign’s use of facebook data, to highlight the fact that such practices are bipartisan.

however, people who downloaded the obama campaign app were aware they were using a political app. by contrast, the data obtained by cambridge analytica was obtained via a personality quiz application whose users had no idea their data would be used by a political campaign.

cambridge analytica improperly obtained the personal information of millions of facebook users to build profiles of us voters in order to target them with personalised political advertisements, via a related uk-based entity called scl elections.
.
- we exploited facebook to harvest millions of people’s profiles, said wylie in march. - and built models to exploit what we knew about them and target their inner demons. that was the basis the entire company was built on.

wylie has previously told mps at a british select committee that the eu referendum was won through fraud after vote leave allegedly used a network of companies to get round election spending laws. he said he thought there “could have been a different outcome had there not been, in my view, cheating”. he also met privately with house democrats in april, but wednesday’s hearing was his first public appearance before us lawmakers.

olivia solon
the guardian

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

zapowiada się bardzo wymowna historia! 📚opis wydawcy 📚

co zrobiłyby kobiety, gdyby nagle liczba słów, które wypowiadają każdego dnia, uległa drastycznemu ograniczeniu?

feministyczna dystopia o świecie rządzonym przez mężczyzn, w którym kobiety mogą wypowiedzieć tylko 100 słów dziennie. mocna, wzbudzająca emocje książka, ważny głos w epoce ruchu #metoo i w świetle ogólnoświatowych dyskusji o prawach kobiet.

czarna bransoletka zaciśnięta na nadgarstku. cyfrowe znaczki układają się w liczbę 15. liczba wypowiedzianych słów nie może przekroczyć 100, każde kolejne słowo oznacza coraz silniejszy ładunek elektryczny. licznik zresetuje się o północy.

zasady są proste: najlepiej usunąć wszystkie językowe ozdobniki, ograniczyć pytania do tych, na które wystarczy odpowiedzieć „tak” lub „nie”. nie pytać dzieci, jak poszło w szkole. nie rozmawiać z mężem, nie wdawać się w dyskusje. ważyć każde słowo.

text:
survivors of  sexual abuse often can’t stand to have sex or just go through the motions without joy, connection, or orgasm. laura davis, author of allies in healing: when the person you love was sexually abused as a child, explains, “partners always tell me they can’t stand being sexually rejected when they had nothing to do with the abuse. i ask them: ‘do you want to make love with someone who isn’t there? someone totally disconnected, and just going through the motions?’ they always say, ‘i guess not.’”
.
.
.

text:
our director leila discussing the importance of vault festival as part of a reviews hub interview below. image: ali wright 
there are plenty of shows to see at this year’s vault festival, happening right now in the arches down under waterloo station, but for the more adventurous the festival also offers a whole host of immersive experiences. greyscale lets audiences decide whether or not they have witnessed an assault, and the reviews hub’s richard maguire met one of its creators, leila sykes.
so what is the show about?
leila doesn’t want to give too much away, but she does reveal that only 10 audience members are present at each show and that they will hear two monologues, one from each of the main protagonists. it’s likely that the audience will meet its first actor outside in the smoking area, so she suggests that people wrap up warmly.
greyscale is influenced by the #metoo campaign, particularly the case of aziz ansari, an american comedian. in january 2018 a woman with the pseudonym of grace accused ansari of sexual assault. ansari has maintained that what happened on their date was fun and consensual. some people thought that the #metoo campaign was overreaching while others thought the incident plainly showed a world of misogyny. like its title suggests, greyscale investigates this grey area, this contested space.
written by madeline gould and joel samuels. greyscale follows a man and woman on their first date around waterloo station. the audience follow them too, stopping off in a pub and even in a ‘structure’ that the producers have built specifically for the show. fascinatingly, gould and samuels were not allowed to confer when they wrote the piece, and so the audience will hear two very different accounts of the same incident. leila hopes that the audience will ask the actors questions in order that the truth, if there is any, can be discovered.
leila is pleased to be back at the vault festival, after her show, with writer madeline, did so well last year.
name: AIAW Theatre Company

text:
are you one of those people that feels miserable when it is raining? ⛈
you look outside and wish it wasn't... 😔

it is not inevitable that it is going to rain? (or at least we would like to hope it would rain for our own wellbeing)

you are literally wishing away your time, you are feeling miserable with something that happens naturally. it affects the core of your emotions.

learn to smile ☺️ when it is raining, realise it is helping you to drink, eat and live the life you want to live.

then think about how many other parts of your life this is affecting? 
perspective is how you turn a miserable thought process into a positive one.

how do you think people in barren deserts feel? 
i'll leave that one with you. ☀️ follow @jamesmalins

text:
🚧🎥 when your street becomes a film set... building incredible fake oldie shop fronts onto the building façades. cool... but. 
it’s a polanski, which doesn’t sit well with me. like #metoo stops at him in france. the guy still hasn’t been tried. which just sends the message to all victims « if he’s talented and high profile enough he can be accused of raping a 13 year old and flee justice and still live a charmed life protected by the french government ». not to mention that he probably got funding from the state for his film too. 
oh and the cherry on the cynical cake? the film is about the dreyfus affair, a famous turn of the 20th century case of an anti-semitic miscarriage of justice... between the lines? polanski is a victim too ... 🤮
#norestforthewicked #whoswithme #metoo #noexceptions #talentisnoexcuse #fairtrial #respectvictims #respecthistory #cynical #filmset #rantover #paris ***
🚧🎥 quand ta rue devient un décor de cinéma... construction de devantures de boutiques sur les façades des immeubles. la classe... sauf que. 
c’est un polanski. et ça, ça ne passe pas. comme si l’ère #metoo s’arrêtait à sa porte. c’est comme dire à toutes les victimes « si un homme est suffisamment connu et talentueux, il peut être accusé d’avoir violé une enfant de 13 ans, fuir la justice, et le gouvernement français le protègera ». et le pire c’est que l’état a sans doute contribué au financement du film.
sans oublier la cerise sur ce gateau de cynisme : c’est un film sur l’affaire dreyfus. donc entre les lignes, polanski se pose en victime de la justice et de l’anti-sémitisme... 🤮
#justicepourtous #metoo #pasdexception #respectdesvictimes #respectdelhistoire #torchonsserviettes #quiestavecmoi #gueulante #tournage #paris

text:
festivali i parë i rëndësishëm i filmit evropian për këtë vit, berlinalja, është hapur tashmë me një deklaratë kundër seksizmit në industrinë e filmit, e duke mirëpritur një numër të paprecedentë regjisoresh femra.

eventi 11 ditor konsiderohet si një nga më të rëndësishmit dhe prezanton 400 filma nga e gjithë bota, dedikuar temave nga më të ndryshmet.

por, edhe tapeti i kuq i tij premton jo pak, me kristian bejl, dajan kruger, tilda suinton, catherine deneuve, jonah hill, chiwetel ejiofor, casey affleck dhe juliette binoche, që këtë vit është edhe presidente e jurisë.
sinkron juliette binoche, presidente e jurisë së berlinales
“ne do t’i përdorim njohuritë, eksperiencën, mendjen tonë, për të gjykuar se cilët janë filmat më të mirë”, tha juliette binoche, presidente e jurisë së berlinales.

binoche, 54 vjeç, do të kryesojë një panel prej gjashtë anëtarësh, në zgjedhjen e fituesit të çmimeve prestigjoze “ariu i artë” dhe “ariu i argjendtë”, që do të ndahen në një ceremoni gala më 16 shkurt.

vitin e kaluar, me lëvizjen #metoo që kish mbërthyer industrinë, dokudrama inovative “mos më prek” e rumunes adina pintilie, mori çmimet kryesore.

text:
ok let’s take a little minute to chat about something very near to my heart

across the world - from the workplace to education to politics - women are still facing prejudice, intolerance and inequality

people…it's 2019!

with global campaigns to empower women relying on the support of men to advance the cause, it’s frustrating to see the lack of progress in gender equality in our social, cultural and economic systems. 👷🏽‍♀️as a civil engineer having worked on a construction site building roads and bridges i can tell you first hand the gross inequality in that industry alone.

and yet all it takes is one woman to make a change.

one woman to not stand for it any longer.

the suffragettes

the #metoo advocators

my female mentor on the construction site who used to stand up to the men every single day, despite harsh criticism.

i’m so grateful for the women who have paved the way so that i can have the privileges that we so often take for granted 💖 💎💎💎💎💎💎 each year the @managersandleaders host an international womens day great debate!

it’s such an incredible day and brings attention to important topics that we should be talking about openly

this year, the institute challenges the notion: "do women need the cooperation of men to succeed in 2019?” ooh kinda gets me fired up just thinking about it!! 🔥🔥🔥 i’m going to the sydney event - did you wanna come with and sit at the same table!?! it’s such a fun day! would love to meet up 👯‍♀️ here’s the link to the event, it’s on the 8th march, would love to sit with you https://iml.click/2rm7bgc

and tag the woman in your life who inspires you the most!! #iwdgreatdebate #balanceforbetter  #iwd2019

text:
2/2 המשך לפוסט הקודם: 
4) הכתבה כמובן מסתיימת ב...פניה ללב שלנו?
נכון, אנחנו בעידן של #metoo וזה חשוב שקרבנות יצאו ויספרו את מה שעברו.
אבל לא, אנחנו לא יוצאים נגד הילד המתלונן כי הוא "הגיע למייקל ג'קסון".
אנחנו יוצאים נגד הילד המתלונן כי אנחנו יודעים שהוא משקר על סמך העובדות בשטח. אחלה שזאת תקופה של #metoo, אבל אם מישהו משקר אז הוא משקר, התקופה הזאת לא אומרת שצריך אוטומטית להאמין לכל טענה גם אם היא מופרכת לחלוטין.
ולא צריך סרטון שלו כילד קטן מגן על מייקל, ניסיון נחמד להגחיך את טענות ה"מעריצים האדוקים". אני יכול להסתמך על סרטונים שלו מגן על מייקל במשך 20 שנה, עד גיל 30 בערך.
הוא הגן על מייקל כאדם בוגר תחת שבועה בבית המשפט וכשנשאל בפירוט על מה שהוא עשה עם מייקל ג'קסון לא היה בפירוט הזה שום דבר מיני.

רק בשנת 2012, 3 שנים אחרי שמייקל כבר לא יכול להגן על עצמו וכשחשבון הבנק של ידידנו המתלונן התחיל לתת את אותותיו - הוא פתאום "הבין" שמייקל כן אנס אותו והוא פשוט לא פירש את הדברים כהטרדה מינית (כן, רק בגיל 30 הוא ידע לפרש איבר מין שחודר לרקטום שלו וגורם לדימום כהטרדה מינית... עד גיל 30, כל עוד חשבון הבנק שלו היה סבבה, זה היה נראה לו אקט לגיטימי). אגב, חודשיים לפני שהוא "הבין" שזאת הטרדה מינית הוא ביקש לקחת חלק ביצירה של מופע מחווה למייקל בלאס וגאס. האנשים שאחראים על העיזבון של מייקל סרבו לתת לו את התפקיד, אולי גם זה עזר לו פתאום להבין שהוא הוטרד?
גם כשאותי דוחים אני מרגיש קצת מוטרד... פוסט של
barak ortman
6.2.2019
2/2

@lironzaid @thenewsil @rafir

stop_filter_tweet: 2/2 המשך לפוסט הקודם : 4 ) הכתבה כמובן מסתיימת ב ... פניה ללב שלנו ? נכון , אנחנו בעידן של וזה חשוב שקרבנות יצאו ויספרו את מה שעברו . אבל לא , אנחנו לא יוצאים נגד הילד המתלונן כי הוא `` הגיע למייקל ג'קסון '' . אנחנו יוצאים נגד הילד המתלונן כי אנחנו יודעים שהוא משקר על סמך העובדות בשטח . אחלה שזאת תקופה של אבל אם מישהו משקר אז הוא משקר , התקופה הזאת לא אומרת שצריך אוטומטית להאמין לכל טענה גם אם היא מופרכת לחלוטין . ולא צריך סרטון שלו כילד קטן מגן על מייקל , ניסיון נחמד להגחיך את טענות ה '' מעריצים האדוקים '' . אני יכול להסתמך על סרטונים שלו מגן על מייקל במשך 20 שנה , עד גיל 30 בערך . הוא הגן על מייקל כאדם בוגר תחת שבועה בבית המשפט וכשנשאל בפירוט על מה שהוא עשה עם מייקל ג'קסון לא היה בפירוט הזה שום דבר מיני . רק בשנת 2012 , 3 שנים אחרי שמייקל כבר לא יכול להגן על עצמו וכשחשבון הבנק של ידידנו המתלונן התחיל לתת את אותותיו - הוא פתאום `` הבין '' שמייקל כן אנס אותו והוא פשוט לא פירש את הדברים כהטרדה מינית ( כן , רק בגיל 30 הוא ידע לפרש איבר מין שחודר לרקטום שלו וגורם לדימום כהטרדה מינית ... עד גיל 30 , כל עוד חשבון הבנק שלו היה סבבה , זה היה נראה לו אקט לגיטימי ) . אגב , חודשיים לפני שהוא `` הבין '' שזאת הטרדה מינית הוא ביקש לקחת חלק ביצירה של מופע מחווה למייקל בלאס וגאס . האנשים שאחראים על העיזבון של מייקל סרבו לתת לו את התפקיד , אולי גם זה עזר לו פתאום להבין שהוא הוטרד ? גם כשאותי דוחים אני מרגיש קצת מוטרד ... פוסט של barak oman 6.2.2019 2/2 afir

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
in his first post-white house interviews, steve bannon, the rightwing ideologue who helped propel donald trump to the white house, made clear that he had no intention of going quietly. - i’ve got my hands back on my weapons, the former white house chief strategist, who returned as executive chairman of breitbart news late friday afternoon, told the weekly standard. - i built a f***ing machine at breitbart. and now i’m about to go back, knowing what i know, and we’re about to rev that machine up. and rev it up we will do.

just hours after his departure from the trump administration became public, breitbart, whose traffic and advertising have fallen significantly since trump’s election, trumpeted the return of their “populist hero” on its homepage. - the populist-nationalist movement got a lot stronger today, breitbart editor-in-chief alex marlow said in the publication’s announcement post. - breitbart gained an executive chairman with his finger on the pulse of the trump agenda.

the fall of steve bannon is a win for the globalists. but will it last?

also on friday, the once-again head of breitbart told bloomberg news: - if there’s any confusion out there, let me clear it up: i’m leaving the white house and going to war for trump against his opponents – on capitol hill, in the media, and in corporate america.

the 63-year-old also retains the backing of hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. the pair met on wednesday to plot their future plans, bloomberg reported.

julia carrie wong
the guardian

in his first post-white house interviews, steve bannon, the rightwing ideologue who helped propel donald trump to the white house, made clear that he had no intention of going quietly. - i’ve got my hands back on my weapons, the former white house chief strategist, who returned as executive chairman of breitba news late friday afternoon, told the weekly standard. - i built a f***ing machine at breitba. and now i’m about to go back, knowing what i know, and we’re about to rev that machine up. and rev it up we will do.

just hours after his depaure from the trump administration became public, breitba, whose traffic and adveising have fallen significan notly since trump’s election, trumpeted the return of their “populist hero” on its homepage. - the populist-nationalist movement got a lot stronger today, breitba editor-in-chief alex marlow said in the publication’s announcement post. - breitba gained an executive chairman with his finger on the pulse of the trump agenda.

the fall of steve bannon is a win for the globalists. but will it last?

also on friday, the once-again head of breitba told bloomberg news: - if there’s any confusion out there, let me clear it up: i’m leaving the white house and going to war for trump against his opponents – on capitol hill, in the media, and in corporate america.

the 63-year-old also retains the backing of hedge-fund billionaire robe mercer. the pair met on wednesday to plot their future plans, bloomberg repoed.

julia carrie wong
the guardian

text:
- this was steve bannon's baby," said former contractor christopher wylie, who described cambridge analytica as "bannon's arsenal of weaponry to wage a culture war on america using military strategies."
.
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
have you heard about our support for supporters groups in hastings and eastbourne? (with a brighton one on the way too) 
it will be a safe and confidential space for supporters to come together to share strategies and insight on helping loved ones cope with similar issues.

before joining your first session at the group, there’s a 90 minute workshop to attend. this will look at the possible impact of these experiences on the person you care about, but also how this might impact on you.

hastings: (2nd monday of month) : 11th february, 11th march, 8th april, 13th may, 10th june, 8th july

eastbourne: (3rd thursday of month apart from dec) : 21st february, 21st march, 18th april, 16th may, 20th june

to find out exact times/locations or book onto a workshop, please get in touch on helen@survivorsnetwork.org.uk or call the main office on 01273 203380.

#metoo #support #survivors #eastbourne #hastings #groupwork #peersupport

text:
bolly.id - gerakan #meto yang digerakkan oleh aktris tanushree dutta mengejutkan banyak orang. pasalnya, semenjak gerakan ini dikampanyekan, banyak nama-nama besar yang terjerat dalam kasus ini. sebut saja, nana patekar, alok nath, rajkumar hirani, sajid khan, dan pembuat film soumik sen.

aktris madhuri dixit mengatakan dia terkejut membaca nama-nama tersebut terlibat dalam kasus pelecehan seksual. sebagai aktris yang pernah bekerja sama dengan alokh nath dan pembuat film soumik sen mengaku tidak mengetahui rahasia kepribadian mereka. dalam gerakan #metoo, yang melanda bollywood pada agustus tahun lalu, alokh dituduh melakukan pemerkosaan oleh penulis-sutradara vinta nanda. soumik yang menyutradarai film gulaab gang, telah dituduh melakukan perilaku yang tidak pantas oleh tiga wanita. “itu selalu mengejutkan. karena kau sudah mengenal mereka dan kau belum mengenal mereka seperti itu. itu selalu mengejutkan ketika sesuatu seperti itu keluar. apa yang kau kenal dan apa yang kau baca adalah dua orang yang berbeda. itu sangat mengejutkan," komentar madhuri kepada pti. 
madhuri dixit akan segera terlihat dalam film komedi total dhamaal pada 22 februari mendatang. disutradarai oleh indra kumar, total dhamaal, juga dibinyangi anil kapoor, ajay devgn, arshad warsi, riteish deshmukh, johnny lever, boman irani, dan sanjay mishra. (vd)

#madhuridixit #metoo

tweet_full:
bolly.id - gerakan #meto yang digerakkan oleh aktris tanushree dutta mengejutkan banyak orang. pasalnya, semenjak gerakan ini dikampanyekan, banyak nama-nama besar yang terjerat dalam kasus ini. sebut saja, a patekar, alok nath, rajkumar hirani, sajid khan, dan pembuat film soumik sen.

aktris madhuri dixit mengatakan dia terkejut membaca nama-nama tersebut terlibat dalam kasus pelecehan seksual. sebagai aktris yang pernah bekerja sama dengan alokh nath dan pembuat film soumik sen mengaku tidak mengetahui rahasia kepribadian mereka. dalam gerakan #metoo, yang melanda bollywood pada agustus tahun lalu, alokh dituduh melakukan pemerkosaan oleh penulis-sutradara vinta da. soumik yang menyutradarai film gulaab gang, telah dituduh melakukan perilaku yang tidak pantas oleh tiga wanita. “itu selalu mengejutkan. karena kau sudah mengenal mereka dan kau belum mengenal mereka seperti itu. itu selalu mengejutkan ketika sesuatu seperti itu keluar. apa yang kau kenal dan apa yang kau baca adalah dua orang yang berbeda. itu sangat mengejutkan," komentar madhuri kepada pti. 
madhuri dixit akan segera terlihat dalam film komedi total dhamaal pada 22 februari mendatang. disutradarai oleh indra kumar, total dhamaal, juga dibinyangi anil kapoor, ajay devgn, arshad warsi, riteish deshmukh, johnny lever, boman irani, dan sanjay mishra. (vd)

#madhuridixit #metoo
